ummoned creatures cannot touch-attack the warded creature; if also good-aligned, apply #1 as well.","link":""},"push":{"name":"Push","level":"1","school":"School: Conjuration/Summoning","range":"10 ft. + 3 ft./level","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"Fast","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"The caster points, and a target is pushed directly away. The force is roughly one pound per caster level, sufficient to shift small objects or throw opponents off balance.\nNotes:\n    A small object is pushed 10 feet away.\n    If used against a weapon held by a creature, the wielder suffers a penalty “to hit” equal to the caster’s level (e.g., a 10th-level magic-user imposes –10).\n    A creature or heavier object may be moved only if its weight (in pounds) is not more than 50 × caster level.","notes":"The caster points, and a target is pushed directly away. The force is roughly one pound per caster level, sufficient to shift small objects or throw opponents off balance.\nNotes:\n    A small object is pushed 10 feet away.\n    If used against a weapon held by a creature, the wielder suffers a penalty “to hit” equal to the caster’s level (e.g., a 10th-level magic-user imposes –10).\n    A creature or heavier object may be moved only if its weight (in pounds) is not more than 50 × caster level.","link":""},"read magic":{"name":"Read Magic","level":"1","school":"School: Divination","range":"Touch","duration":"2 rounds/level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Allows the caster to read magical writings created by others. The caster’s own magical writings are always readable without this spell.\nNotes:\n    Reading magical script does not normally activate it (unless cursed).\n    Once a particular magical text has been read with this spell, it may be read again later without further use of read magic.\nReverse: Encrypt Magic (below).\nENCRYPT MAGIC (Reverse of Read Magic)\n