de at +1.\n    The shield is frontal only; no benefit vs. attacks from behind or rear flanks.\n    Does not “stack” with worn armor, shields, bracers, etc. Use whichever AC is better; the magic-missile immunity and frontal save bonus still apply.","link":""},"shocking grasp":{"name":"Shocking Grasp","level":"1","school":"School: Transmutation","range":"Touch","duration":"Until discharged (one successful touch)","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S","ct":"Fast","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"The caster’s hand is charged with electricity. The charge is discharged by a successful touch attack (or through conductive material such as metal).\nNotes:\n    Damage: 1d8 + 1 per caster level (electrical).\n    If the caster misses the touch attack, the spell is not lost; the caster may try again until it is discharged.\n    While holding the charge, the caster cannot cast spells requiring somatic or material components.\n    The caster cannot discharge the spell automatically when struck; the caster must hit (or otherwise discharge through a conductor).\n    Not powerful enough to conduct dangerously through a significant volume of water; a small puddle may suffice.","notes":"The caster’s hand is charged with electricity. The charge is discharged by a successful touch attack (or through conductive material such as metal).\nNotes:\n    Damage: 1d8 + 1 per caster level (electrical).\n    If the caster misses the touch attack, the spell is not lost; the caster may try again until it is discharged.\n    While holding the charge, the caster cannot cast spells requiring somatic or material components.\n    The caster cannot discharge the spell automatically when struck; the caster must hit (or otherwise discharge through a conductor).\n    Not powerful enough to conduct dangerously through a significant volume of water; a small puddle may suffice.","link":""},"sleep":{"name":"Sleep","level":"1","school":"School: Enchantment","range":"30 ft. + 10 ft./level","duration":"5 rounds/level","aoe":"15 ft. radius (see below)","components":"V, S, M","ct":"Fast","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Creatures within a 15-foot radius fall into deep magical slumber. The number affected depends on Hit Dice (each HD category rolled separately). Creatures with more than 4+4 HD are unaffected.\nNotes:\n    Sleeping victims may be slain or bound at a rate of one per round per attacker if no foe is in melee range.\n    If melee continues, sleeping victims may be attacked at twice the normal rate, automatically hit, for maximum damage.\n    A sleeping creature requires a full round to awaken and must be shaken or struck; loud noise does not rouse sleepers.\nSleep Spell Effectiveness:\nHit Dice\tNumber Affected\n1 or less\t4d4\n1+ to 2\t2d4\n2+ to 3\t1d4\n3+ to 4\t1d2\n4+1 to 4+4\t0 or 1 (d2–1)\nAbove 4+4\t0\nWeaker creatures in the same category are affected first.","notes":"Creatures within a 15-foot radius fall into deep magical slumber. The number affected depends on Hit Dice (each HD category rolled separately). Creatures with more than 4+4 HD are unaffected.\nNotes:\n    Sleeping victims may be slain or bound at a rate of one per round per attacker if no foe is in melee range.\n    If melee continues, sleeping victims may be attacked at twice the normal rate, automatically hit, for maximum damage.\n    A sleeping creature requires a full round to awaken and must be shaken or struck; loud noise does not rouse sleepers.\nSleep Spell Effectiveness:\nHit Dice\tNumber Affected\n1 or less\t4d4\n1+ to 2\t2d4\n2+ to 3\t1d4\n3+ to 4\t1d2\n4+1 to 4+4\t0 or 1 (d2–1)\nAbove 4+4\t0\nWeaker creatures in the same category are affected first.","link":""},"spider climb":{"name":"Spider Climb","level":"1","school":"School: Transmutation","range":"Touch","duration":"1 round + 1 round/level","aoe":"One willing creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"Fast","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"The subject’s hands and feet become adhesive, permitting climbing walls and ceilings with no chance of falling. Climbing movement is 30 ft. per round.\nNotes:\nThe subject finds delicate manipulation difficult while the spell lasts.","notes":"The subject’s hands and feet become adhesive, permitting climbing walls and ceilings with no chance of falling. Climbing movement is 30 ft. per round.\nNotes:\nThe subject finds delicate manipulation difficult while the spell lasts.","link":""},"tanzur s floating disk":{"name":"Tanzur’S Floating Disk","level":"1","school":"School: Evocation","range":"20 ft.","duration":"3 turns + 1 turn/level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"Fast","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Conjures an invisible disk about 3 feet across, shaped like a shallow bowl. It floats and moves by the caster’s command, but disappears if more than 20 feet from the caster.\nNotes:\n    Maximum speed: 60 ft. per round.\n    Capacity: 100 lbs. per caster level.","notes":"Conjures an invisible disk about 3 feet across, shaped like a shallow bowl. It floats and moves by the caster’s command, but disappears if more than 20 feet from the caster.\nNotes:\n    Maximum speed: 60 ft. per round.\n    Capacity: 100 lbs. per caster level.","link":""},"unseen servant":{"name":"Unseen Servant","level":"1","school":"School: Conjuration/Summoning","range":"Caster","duration":"6 turns + 1 turn/level","aoe":"30 ft. radius around caster","components":"V, S, M","ct":"Fast","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Summons a mindless force that performs simple tasks (fetching, carrying, opening doors, cleaning, holding chairs, mending, etc.) until given a new command.\nNotes:\n    Maximum force/carrying capacity: 20 lbs.\n    Cannot attack.\n    Cannot move beyond the spell’s area of effect (which moves with the caster).","notes":"Summons a mindless force that performs simple tasks (fetching, carrying, opening doors, cleaning, holding chairs, mending, etc.) until given a new command.\nNotes:\n    Maximum force/carrying capacity: 20 lbs.\n    Cannot attack.\n    Cannot move beyond the spell’s area of effect (which moves with the caster).","link":""},"ventriloquism":{"name":"Ventriloquism","level":"1","school":"School: Illusion","range":"10 ft./level (maximum 60 ft.)","duration":"2 rounds + 1 round/level","aoe":"One object or point in space","components":"V, M","ct":"Fast","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"The caster’s voice (or any vocalized sound) appears to come from another location: behind a door, down a corridor, from a statue, etc.\nNotes:\nFor each point of the listener’s Intelligence above 12, there is a cumulative 10% chance to detect the true source. Otherwise, the sound is believed to originate from the chosen point.","notes":"The caster’s voice (or any vocalized sound) appears to come from another location: behind a door, down a corridor, from a statue, etc.\nNotes:\nFor each point of the listener’s Intelligence above 12, there is a cumulative 10% chance to detect the true source. Otherwise, the sound is believed to originate from the chosen point.","link":""},"write":{"name":"Write","level":"1","school":"School: Evocation","range":"Caster","duration":"1 hour/level","aoe":"Caster","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None (special; see below)","save_type":"","description":"This spell allows the caster to copy a spell into a spell book even if the spell is of higher level than the caster can currently cast. The process is dangerous.\nNotes:\nThe caster must save vs. spells with a modifier based on the spell being transcribed:\n    Spell is up to 1 level higher than the caster can cast: +2 to save.\n    Spell is 2 levels higher: no modifier.\n    More than 2 levels higher: –1 per additional level beyond 2.\nFailure: the spell is not copied; the caster takes 1d4 damage per spell level attempted and is unconscious for 1 turn per hit point of damage suffered. This damage cannot be healed faster than 4 hp/day, even by magical healing.\nSuccess: the spell may be copied, requiring 1 hour per spell level.\nMaterial component: ink costing at least 200 gp.","notes":"This spell allows the caster to copy a spell into a spell book even if the spell is of higher level than the caster can currently cast. The process is dangerous.\nNotes:\nThe caster must save vs. spells with a modifier based on the spell being transcribed:\n    Spell is up to 1 level higher than the caster can cast: +2 to save.\n    Spell is 2 levels higher: no modifier.\n    More than 2 levels higher: –1 per additional level beyond 2.\nFailure: the spell is not copied; the caster takes 1d4 damage per spell level attempted and is unconscious for 1 turn per hit point of damage suffered. This damage cannot be healed faster than 4 hp/day, even by magical healing.\nSuccess: the spell may be copied, requiring 1 hour per spell level.\nMaterial component: ink costing at least 200 gp.","link":""},"audible glamour":{"name":"Audible Glamour","level":"2","school":"School: Illusion","range":"60 ft. + 10 ft./level","duration":"2 rounds/level","aoe":"Within hearing distance of a chosen point","components":"V, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"Special (see below)","save_type":"","description":"This spell creates illusory sounds issuing from a point in space within range (the “focal point”). The caster determines the nature of the sounds, but their maximum loudness is limited by caster level.\nNotes:\n    The caster may move the focal point at will (so long as it remains within range) until the spell ends.\n    Any type of sound may be created. A 3rd-level caster can produce noise equivalent to four people shouting (or less). Each additional caster level adds the equivalent of four more people.\n    As a benchmark, the sound of an explosion or landslide generally requires about an 8th-level caster.\n    Saving throws are allowed only if a listener has reason to doubt the sound. Players must declare disbelief; the referee determines disbelief for monsters and NPCs based on circumstances and plausibility.","notes":"This spell creates illusory sounds issuing from a point in space within range (the “focal point”). The caster determines the nature of the sounds, but their maximum loudness is limited by caster level.\nNotes:\n    The caster may move the focal point at will (so long as it remains within range) until the spell ends.\n    Any type of sound may be created. A 3rd-level caster can produce noise equivalent to four people shouting (or less). Each additional caster level adds the equivalent of four more people.\n    As a benchmark, the sound of an explosion or landslide generally requires about an 8th-level caster.\n    Saving throws are allowed only if a listener has reason to doubt the sound. Players must declare disbelief; the referee determines disbelief for monsters and NPCs based on circumstances and plausibility.","link":""},"continual light":{"name":"Continual Light","level":"2","school":"School: Transmutation","range":"10 ft./level","duration":"1 turn + 1 round/level","aoe":"15 ft. radius sphere","components":"V, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"Special (see below)","save_type":"","description":"Creates bright light centered on a creature, object, or point in space, illuminating everything within 60 feet.\nNotes:\n    If cast into magical darkness, continual light and the darkness effect cancel.\n    The light is stationary unless cast upon a moving creature or object, in which case it moves with the target.\n    If targeted at a creature’s eyes or other sense organs, the creature may save vs. spells (apply Dexterity saving throw modifier if used).\n        Success: the light appears just behind the creature (stationary in the air).\n        Failure: the creature is effectively blinded until the spell ends or is dispelled.\n    The caster may have no more than three continual light spells in effect at once; casting a fourth ends the earliest one still running.\n    At the end of each full month the spell persists, there is a 1 in 12 chance it ends.\n    The arcane version cannot be reversed to create continual darkness.\nDARKNESS, 15-FOOT RADIUS\nLevel: 2\nSchool: Transmutation\nCreates magical darkness centered on a creature, object, or point in space. The caster may dismiss it at will. No light source (even magical light such as a glowing blade) illuminates the area, though a light spell may counter it. Infravision does not function within the darkness.\nNotes:\n    If targeted on a light source, the light is extinguished for the duration, but no additional field of darkness is created.\n    The darkness is stationary unless cast upon a moving creature or object; it cannot be “commanded” to move after casting.\n    If cast upon a creature, the target may save vs. spells (apply Dexterity saving throw modifier if used).\n        Success: the darkness appears as a stationary point just behind the creature rather than affecting it.","notes":"Creates bright light centered on a creature, object, or point in space, illuminating everything within 60 feet.\nNotes:\n    If cast into magical darkness, continual light and the darkness effect cancel.\n    The light is stationary unless cast upon a moving creature or object, in which case it moves with the target.\n    If targeted at a creature’s eyes or other sense organs, the creature may save vs. spells (apply Dexterity saving throw modifier if used).\n        Success: the light appears just behind the creature (stationary in the air).\n        Failure: the creature is effectively blinded until the spell ends or is dispelled.\n    The caster may have no more than three continual light spells in effect at once; casting a fourth ends the earliest one still running.\n    At the end of each full month the spell persists, there is a 1 in 12 chance it ends.\n    The arcane version cannot be reversed to create continual darkness.\nDARKNESS, 15-FOOT RADIUS\nLevel: 2\nSchool: Transmutation\nCreates magical darkness centered on a creature, object, or point in space. The caster may dismiss it at will. No light source (even magical light such as a glowing blade) illuminates the area, though a light spell may counter it. Infravision does not function within the darkness.\nNotes:\n    If targeted on a light source, the light is extinguished for the duration, but no additional field of darkness is created.\n    The darkness is stationary unless cast upon a moving creature or object; it cannot be “commanded” to move after casting.\n    If cast upon a creature, the target may save vs. spells (apply Dexterity saving throw modifier if used).\n        Success: the darkness appears as a stationary point just behind the creature rather than affecting it.","link":""},"detect evil":{"name":"Detect Evil","level":"2","school":"School: Divination","range":"Caster","duration":"5 rounds/level","aoe":"10 ft. wide by 60 ft. long path","components":"V, S","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Reveals emanations of evil within the beam-like area of effect.\nNotes:\n    Detects evil, not danger: it will not reveal mundane traps, poison, or similar hazards.\n    Does not detect cursed items unless the curse renders the item inherently evil.\nReverse: Detect Good (below).\nDETECT GOOD (Reverse of Detect Evil)\nLevel: 2\nSchool: Divination\nReveals emanations of good alignment within the beam-like area of effect.\nNotes:\n    Detects good alignment, not general benefit: it will not reveal healing potions or most magic items unless they are inherently holy.","notes":"Reveals emanations of evil within the beam-like area of effect.\nNotes:\n    Detects evil, not danger: it will not reveal mundane traps, poison, or similar hazards.\n    Does not detect cursed items unless the curse renders the item inherently evil.\nReverse: Detect Good (below).\nDETECT GOOD (Reverse of Detect Evil)\nLevel: 2\nSchool: Divination\nReveals emanations of good alignment within the beam-like area of effect.\nNotes:\n    Detects good alignment, not general benefit: it will not reveal healing potions or most magic items unless they are inherently holy.","link":""},"detect invisibility":{"name":"Detect Invisibility","level":"2","school":"School: Divination","range":"Caster","duration":"5 rounds/level","aoe":"Caster (see below)","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Allows the caster to see invisible and hidden things, and to see into the Astral and Ethereal planes.\nNotes:\nThe magical sight functions in a 10-foot-wide path extending 10 ft./level.","notes":"Allows the caster to see invisible and hidden things, and to see into the Astral and Ethereal planes.\nNotes:\nThe magical sight functions in a 10-foot-wide path extending 10 ft./level.","link":""},"esp":{"name":"Esp","level":"2","school":"School: Divination","range":"Caster","duration":"1 round/level","aoe":"5 ft. radius/level (maximum 90 ft.)","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Permits the caster to overhear the surface thoughts of any thinking creature within the area of effect.\nNotes:\n    Line of sight is not required; the spell can be used through doors and similar barriers.\n    It cannot penetrate more than 2 feet of stone or 2 inches of metal, and is blocked by even a thin sheet of lead.","notes":"Permits the caster to overhear the surface thoughts of any thinking creature within the area of effect.\nNotes:\n    Line of sight is not required; the spell can be used through doors and similar barriers.\n    It cannot penetrate more than 2 feet of stone or 2 inches of metal, and is blocked by even a thin sheet of lead.","link":""},"fool s gold":{"name":"Fool’S Gold","level":"2","school":"School: Transmutation","range":"10 ft.","duration":"6 turns/level","aoe":"1 cubic foot/level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"Special (see below)","save_type":"","description":"Transmutes base metal into a metal closely resembling gold (about 1 cubic foot per caster level—roughly 2,000 copper coins).\nNotes:\n    Observers may detect the fraud: if d20 + caster level is ≤ observer’s Intelligence, the deception is noticed. (The referee may choose or roll Intelligence for creatures as needed.)\n    Expensive material components may improve believability, at the referee’s discretion.\n    Mundane tests may reveal the effect; e.g., striking with cold iron may have a 10% chance to revert the metal (exact methods are referee-determined).","notes":"Transmutes base metal into a metal closely resembling gold (about 1 cubic foot per caster level—roughly 2,000 copper coins).\nNotes:\n    Observers may detect the fraud: if d20 + caster level is ≤ observer’s Intelligence, the deception is noticed. (The referee may choose or roll Intelligence for creatures as needed.)\n    Expensive material components may improve believability, at the referee’s discretion.\n    Mundane tests may reveal the effect; e.g., striking with cold iron may have a 10% chance to revert the metal (exact methods are referee-determined).","link":""},"forget":{"name":"Forget","level":"2","school":"School: Enchantment","range":"30 ft.","duration":"Instantaneous (see below)","aoe":"1–4 creatures in a 20 ft. square","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Victims forget events of the immediate past. The spell erases memory of the last round, plus one additional round per three caster levels.\nNotes:\n    The caster chooses which creatures in the area are affected; each makes a saving throw.\n    Saving throw penalty depends on number of targets:\n        1 target: –2\n        2 targets: –1\n        3–4 targets: no penalty\n    Lost memories are restored only by heal, restoration, or wish; the effect is not removed by dispel magic.","notes":"Victims forget events of the immediate past. The spell erases memory of the last round, plus one additional round per three caster levels.\nNotes:\n    The caster chooses which creatures in the area are affected; each makes a saving throw.\n    Saving throw penalty depends on number of targets:\n        1 target: –2\n        2 targets: –1\n        3–4 targets: no penalty\n    Lost memories are restored only by heal, restoration, or wish; the effect is not removed by dispel magic.","link":""},"invisibility":{"name":"Invisibility","level":"2","school":"School: Illusion","range":"Touch","duration":"Special (see below)","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"The subject and all carried gear fade from sight. Infravision does not reveal an invisible creature.\nNotes:\nThe spell ends when:\n    the subject attacks (including casting a spell that directly causes damage),\n    the caster ends the spell, or\n    the effect is dispelled.\nThe spell does not silence the subject or eliminate scent. Invisible creatures can see themselves; the caster cannot (unless also the subject). The spell cannot be cast on an unwilling creature.","notes":"The subject and all carried gear fade from sight. Infravision does not reveal an invisible creature.\nNotes:\nThe spell ends when:\n    the subject attacks (including casting a spell that directly causes damage),\n    the caster ends the spell, or\n    the effect is dispelled.\nThe spell does not silence the subject or eliminate scent. Invisible creatures can see themselves; the caster cannot (unless also the subject). The spell cannot be cast on an unwilling creature.","link":""},"false trap":{"name":"False Trap","level":"2","school":"School: Illusion","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One object","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Creates an illusory trap on an object, convincing to normal inspection (including a thief’s examination).\nNotes:\n    Any examiner has an 80% chance to find and believe the false trap.\n    For thieves, reduce this chance by 3% per level of experience.\n    If a thief attempts to remove the “trap,” there is only a 20% chance the illusion is dispelled or exposed; otherwise the thief typically concludes the attempt failed.\n    Only one false trap may exist within a 50 ft. radius. If two such objects come within 50 ft. of each other, both illusions are dispelled.","notes":"Creates an illusory trap on an object, convincing to normal inspection (including a thief’s examination).\nNotes:\n    Any examiner has an 80% chance to find and believe the false trap.\n    For thieves, reduce this chance by 3% per level of experience.\n    If a thief attempts to remove the “trap,” there is only a 20% chance the illusion is dispelled or exposed; otherwise the thief typically concludes the attempt failed.\n    Only one false trap may exist within a 50 ft. radius. If two such objects come within 50 ft. of each other, both illusions are dispelled.","link":""},"knock":{"name":"Knock","level":"2","school":"School: Transmutation","range":"60 ft.","duration":"Special","aoe":"10 sq. ft./level","components":"V","ct":"Fast","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Opens doors that are stuck, barred, locked, or even wizard locked. Chains and chests may also spring open.\nNotes:\n    Does not open gravity-operated doors such as portcullises.\n    If multiple devices secure a portal, the spell opens only two; a triple-locked door resists a single casting.","notes":"Opens doors that are stuck, barred, locked, or even wizard locked. Chains and chests may also spring open.\nNotes:\n    Does not open gravity-operated doors such as portcullises.\n    If multiple devices secure a portal, the spell opens only two; a triple-locked door resists a single casting.","link":""},"levitate":{"name":"Levitate","level":"2","school":"School: Transmutation","range":"20 ft./level","duration":"1 turn/level","aoe":"Caster or one creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"Special (see below)","save_type":"","description":"Permits the caster to levitate self or another creature, up to 100 lbs. per level.\nNotes:\n    If cast on self: vertical movement at 20 ft./round.\n    If cast on another: vertical movement at 10 ft./round.\n    No saving throw is required for a willing subject. An unwilling subject may save vs. spells to negate.\n    No horizontal movement is granted (aerial agility I), but the levitated creature may pull along surfaces if something can be grasped.","notes":"Permits the caster to levitate self or another creature, up to 100 lbs. per level.\nNotes:\n    If cast on self: vertical movement at 20 ft./round.\n    If cast on another: vertical movement at 10 ft./round.\n    No saving throw is required for a willing subject. An unwilling subject may save vs. spells to negate.\n    No horizontal movement is granted (aerial agility I), but the levitated creature may pull along surfaces if something can be grasped.","link":""},"locate object":{"name":"Locate Object","level":"2","school":"School: Divination","range":"20 ft./level","duration":"1 round/level","aoe":"Special (pathway; usually by turning in place)","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"The caster visualizes an object (general or specific). If an object matching the description is within the pathway-shaped area of effect, the caster learns the exact distance to the nearest such object. Once an object is located, the spell ends.\nNotes:\n    Opaque material does not block the spell; solid rock does not prevent detection.\n    The target must be an object (not a creature or place).\n    Only the nearest matching object is located.\n    The object must be on the same plane.\n    The spell reveals distance/location, not intervening terrain or hazards.\n    The spell cannot be cast unless the caster can visualize the target (familiar with its form, function, and material).\n    Concentration is required; if broken, the spell ends.","notes":"The caster visualizes an object (general or specific). If an object matching the description is within the pathway-shaped area of effect, the caster learns the exact distance to the nearest such object. Once an object is located, the spell ends.\nNotes:\n    Opaque material does not block the spell; solid rock does not prevent detection.\n    The target must be an object (not a creature or place).\n    Only the nearest matching object is located.\n    The object must be on the same plane.\n    The spell reveals distance/location, not intervening terrain or hazards.\n    The spell cannot be cast unless the caster can visualize the target (familiar with its form, function, and material).\n    Concentration is required; if broken, the spell ends.","link":""},"magic mouth":{"name":"Magic Mouth","level":"2","school":"School: Transmutation","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent until triggered","aoe":"One object","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Enchants an object so that, when specified conditions occur, a mouth appears and speaks a preset message of up to 25 words.\nNotes:\n    Trigger conditions are set by the caster, but detection range is limited to 5 ft./level.\n    The mouth cannot detect invisible creatures.\n    It has no senses other than “visual” perception of events (it does not truly see).\n    Triggers must be stated in in-world terms (no game-terms like “hit dice,” “class,” “level,” etc.).","notes":"Enchants an object so that, when specified conditions occur, a mouth appears and speaks a preset message of up to 25 words.\nNotes:\n    Trigger conditions are set by the caster, but detection range is limited to 5 ft./level.\n    The mouth cannot detect invisible creatures.\n    It has no senses other than “visual” perception of events (it does not truly see).\n    Triggers must be stated in in-world terms (no game-terms like “hit dice,” “class,” “level,” etc.).","link":""},"mirror image":{"name":"Mirror Image","level":"2","school":"School: Illusion","range":"Caster","duration":"2 rounds/level","aoe":"6 ft. radius","components":"V, S","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Creates 1d4 illusory duplicates that mimic the caster’s movements. The caster’s immediate area appears subtly blurred, making it impossible to identify the true caster by sight without magical aid (e.g., true seeing).\nNotes:\n    When attacked, determine randomly whether the attack targets the real caster or an image.\n    A hit on an image destroys that image only; others remain.\n    Images fade when the spell ends.","notes":"Creates 1d4 illusory duplicates that mimic the caster’s movements. The caster’s immediate area appears subtly blurred, making it impossible to identify the true caster by sight without magical aid (e.g., true seeing).\nNotes:\n    When attacked, determine randomly whether the attack targets the real caster or an image.\n    A hit on an image destroys that image only; others remain.\n    Images fade when the spell ends.","link":""},"pyrotechnics":{"name":"Pyrotechnics","level":"2","school":"School: Transmutation","range":"120 ft.","duration":"1 round/level.","aoe":"Special (depends on fire source)","components":"V, S","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Requires an existing fire source within range and produces one of two effects: fireworks or smoke. The area depends on the size of the source fire. The source fire is extinguished when the spell is cast.\nNotes:\n    Fireworks:\n        Blinds all creatures in the area of effect and out to 120 ft. beyond (if visible) for 1d4+1 rounds.\n        The display fills 10× the volume of the fire source.\n    Smoke:\n        Cloud fills 100× the volume of the fire source.\n        Vision is obscured beyond 20 ft.","notes":"Requires an existing fire source within range and produces one of two effects: fireworks or smoke. The area depends on the size of the source fire. The source fire is extinguished when the spell is cast.\nNotes:\n    Fireworks:\n        Blinds all creatures in the area of effect and out to 120 ft. beyond (if visible) for 1d4+1 rounds.\n        The display fills 10× the volume of the fire source.\n    Smoke:\n        Cloud fills 100× the volume of the fire source.\n        Vision is obscured beyond 20 ft.","link":""},"ray of enfeeblement":{"name":"Ray of Enfeeblement","level":"2","school":"School: Enchantment","range":"10 ft. + 3 ft./level","duration":"1 round/level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S","ct":"2 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"A ray of unpleasant, indescribable color strikes the target (no attack roll required). If the target fails its save, Strength and all Strength-dependent attack effects are reduced.\nNotes:\n    Base reduction: 25%.\n    Additional reduction: +1% per caster level (rounded as the referee deems convenient).\n    “To hit” rolls are not affected, but damage (and other Strength-based effects) is reduced accordingly.\n    Temporary reduction below class minimums does not affect class status (e.g., a paladin remains a paladin).","notes":"A ray of unpleasant, indescribable color strikes the target (no attack roll required). If the target fails its save, Strength and all Strength-dependent attack effects are reduced.\nNotes:\n    Base reduction: 25%.\n    Additional reduction: +1% per caster level (rounded as the referee deems convenient).\n    “To hit” rolls are not affected, but damage (and other Strength-based effects) is reduced accordingly.\n    Temporary reduction below class minimums does not affect class status (e.g., a paladin remains a paladin).","link":""},"rope trick":{"name":"Rope Trick","level":"2","school":"School: Transmutation","range":"Touch","duration":"2 turns/level","aoe":"One piece of rope","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Enchants a rope so one end becomes a portal to an extra-dimensional pocket. The rope rises and hangs suspended by the portal’s connection.\nNotes:\n    Up to six medium creatures may hide within (or five if the rope is also pulled inside).\n    When the spell ends, creatures or contents still within fall back into normal space.\n    The outside world is visible from within, but cannot be affected from inside.","notes":"Enchants a rope so one end becomes a portal to an extra-dimensional pocket. The rope rises and hangs suspended by the portal’s connection.\nNotes:\n    Up to six medium creatures may hide within (or five if the rope is also pulled inside).\n    When the spell ends, creatures or contents still within fall back into normal space.\n    The outside world is visible from within, but cannot be affected from inside.","link":""},"scare":{"name":"Scare","level":"2","school":"School: Enchantment","range":"10 ft.","duration":"3d4 rounds","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Causes terror in one creature of less than 6th level or 6 HD.\nNotes:\n    If the save succeeds, there is no effect.\n    If the save fails, the creature is nearly frozen in place; it cannot move, though it may fight defensively if attacked.\n    While affected: –1 to attack rolls, damage rolls, and saving throws.","notes":"Causes terror in one creature of less than 6th level or 6 HD.\nNotes:\n    If the save succeeds, there is no effect.\n    If the save fails, the creature is nearly frozen in place; it cannot move, though it may fight defensively if attacked.\n    While affected: –1 to attack rolls, damage rolls, and saving throws.","link":""},"shatter":{"name":"Shatter","level":"2","school":"School: Transmutation","range":"60 ft.","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"One object","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"Yes (item save; see below)","save_type":"","description":"Shatters a brittle item into pieces. The item may save vs. crushing blow to avoid destruction (per the appropriate item saving throw table).\nNotes:\n    Maximum weight: 10 lbs. per level.\n    Only brittle substances (glass, earthenware, etc.) are affected.\n    Magic items are immune (potion bottles are not magical).","notes":"Shatters a brittle item into pieces. The item may save vs. crushing blow to avoid destruction (per the appropriate item saving throw table).\nNotes:\n    Maximum weight: 10 lbs. per level.\n    Only brittle substances (glass, earthenware, etc.) are affected.\n    Magic items are immune (potion bottles are not magical).","link":""},"stinking cloud":{"name":"Stinking Cloud","level":"2","school":"School: Evocation","range":"30 ft.","duration":"1 round/level","aoe":"20 ft. radius spherical cloud","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"Special (see below)","save_type":"","description":"Creates a nauseating vapor cloud at a chosen point within range. Creatures within or entering the cloud must save.\nNotes:\n    Fail save: unable to act for 1d4+1 rounds, retching and gagging (treated as stunned and staggered).\n    Success: the creature may flee the cloud; after one full round breathing fresh air it is free of effects (but is treated as stunned during that one round).\n    Even on a successful save, no creature can do anything within the cloud except attempt to leave as quickly as possible.","notes":"Creates a nauseating vapor cloud at a chosen point within range. Creatures within or entering the cloud must save.\nNotes:\n    Fail save: unable to act for 1d4+1 rounds, retching and gagging (treated as stunned and staggered).\n    Success: the creature may flee the cloud; after one full round breathing fresh air it is free of effects (but is treated as stunned during that one round).\n    Even on a successful save, no creature can do anything within the cloud except attempt to leave as quickly as possible.","link":""},"strength":{"name":"Strength","level":"2","school":"School: Transmutation","range":"Touch","duration":"6 turns/level","aoe":"One person","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Increases the subject’s Strength.\nNotes:\n    Affects only bipedal creatures of Medium size or smaller (human, demihuman, humanoid-like).\n    Strength increases by 1d6; fighters/rangers/paladins add +1 to the die roll.\n    If cast on a monster, the referee may simplify: grant +1 damage, and if the d6 roll is 5–6, also +1 to hit.","notes":"Increases the subject’s Strength.\nNotes:\n    Affects only bipedal creatures of Medium size or smaller (human, demihuman, humanoid-like).\n    Strength increases by 1d6; fighters/rangers/paladins add +1 to the die roll.\n    If cast on a monster, the referee may simplify: grant +1 damage, and if the d6 roll is 5–6, also +1 to hit.","link":""},"web":{"name":"Web","level":"2","school":"School: Evocation","range":"5 ft./level","duration":"2 turns/level","aoe":"Up to 16 squares (anchored), up to 80 ft. high","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"Special (see below)","save_type":"","description":"Creates thick, sticky webs in open areas where they can be anchored (between walls, floor and ceiling, etc.), filling up to 16 five-foot squares (up to 80 ft. × 80 ft.) and up to 80 feet in height.\nNotes:\n    Creatures in the area must save at –2.\n    No creature within the area—whether it saves or not—may attack or cast spells until it escapes.\n    Successful save:\n        If within 5 feet of the edge: the creature leaps free and is unaffected.\n        Otherwise: the creature can force through at twice the speed of one who failed, and cannot suffocate. If Strength is less than 13, this rate is 1 ft./turn (double the failed-save baseline).\n    Failed save:\n        Cumulative 5% chance per turn to suffocate until free.\n        Strength < 13: trapped; cannot move or act.\n        Strength 13–17: move 1 ft./turn.\n        Strength 18+: move 10 ft./turn.\n        Very large creatures (e.g., dragons): break through at 100 ft./turn.\n    The webs are highly flammable; fire flashes through the entire mass, dealing 2d4 damage to all within and burning the webs away.","notes":"Creates thick, sticky webs in open areas where they can be anchored (between walls, floor and ceiling, etc.), filling up to 16 five-foot squares (up to 80 ft. × 80 ft.) and up to 80 feet in height.\nNotes:\n    Creatures in the area must save at –2.\n    No creature within the area—whether it saves or not—may attack or cast spells until it escapes.\n    Successful save:\n        If within 5 feet of the edge: the creature leaps free and is unaffected.\n        Otherwise: the creature can force through at twice the speed of one who failed, and cannot suffocate. If Strength is less than 13, this rate is 1 ft./turn (double the failed-save baseline).\n    Failed save:\n        Cumulative 5% chance per turn to suffocate until free.\n        Strength < 13: trapped; cannot move or act.\n        Strength 13–17: move 1 ft./turn.\n        Strength 18+: move 10 ft./turn.\n        Very large creatures (e.g., dragons): break through at 100 ft./turn.\n    The webs are highly flammable; fire flashes through the entire mass, dealing 2d4 damage to all within and burning the webs away.","link":""},"wizard lock":{"name":"Wizard Lock","level":"2","school":"School: Transmutation","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One door or portal","components":"V, S","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Magically locks a closed door or similar portal as if securely barred. Maximum portal size: 30 sq. ft. per level.\nNotes:\n    The portal must normally open and close and must be closed for the spell to function.\n    A wizard-locked portal may be battered open, but will not open normally.\n    The spell is negated by knock or dispel magic.","notes":"Magically locks a closed door or similar portal as if securely barred. Maximum portal size: 30 sq. ft. per level.\nNotes:\n    The portal must normally open and close and must be closed for the spell to function.\n    A wizard-locked portal may be battered open, but will not open normally.\n    The spell is negated by knock or dispel magic.","link":""},"clairaudience":{"name":"Clairaudience","level":"3","school":"Range: Caster","range":"","duration":"1 round/magic-user level","aoe":"6-ft. radius around target point","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Clairaudience allows you to eavesdrop magically upon a particular location, hearing (but not seeing) what is happening there. There is no effective limit to the spell’s range, but the location must either be familiar to you (you have been there before) or be obvious, such as the top floor inside a tower you can see, or just beyond a dungeon door.\nDetails:\nThe spell cannot penetrate metal; sheets of any type of metal between you and the target area will prevent you from being able to scry upon the area. You can hear sounds in a 6-ft. radius of the spell’s focal point. The spell cannot be used to scry across planes of existence; it is limited to locations in the same plane in which it is cast.","notes":"Clairaudience allows you to eavesdrop magically upon a particular location, hearing (but not seeing) what is happening there. There is no effective limit to the spell’s range, but the location must either be familiar to you (you have been there before) or be obvious, such as the top floor inside a tower you can see, or just beyond a dungeon door.\nDetails:\nThe spell cannot penetrate metal; sheets of any type of metal between you and the target area will prevent you from being able to scry upon the area. You can hear sounds in a 6-ft. radius of the spell’s focal point. The spell cannot be used to scry across planes of existence; it is limited to locations in the same plane in which it is cast.","link":""},"clairvoyance":{"name":"Clairvoyance","level":"3","school":"Range: Caster","range":"","duration":"1 round/magic-user level","aoe":"See below","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Clairvoyance, together with clairaudience, is one of the classic “scrying” spells—spells that allow the caster to extend his or her perception and senses far into the distance to spy upon enemies and scout locations. Clairvoyance is a means of seeing (but not hearing) events in a distant location. There is no effective limit to the spell’s range, but the location must either be familiar to you (you have been there before) or be obvious, such as the top floor inside a tower you can see, or just beyond a dungeon door.\nDetails:\nThe spell cannot penetrate metal; sheets of any type of metal between the caster and the target area will prevent the magic-user from being able to scry upon the area. If the area is dark, you can see in a 10-ft. radius of the spell’s focal point as if the area were illuminated. Infravision does not boost the spell because you are not seeing with your physical eyes.\nIf the area is not dark, you can see as if you were standing at the spell’s focal point, for a normal distance but in all directions at once (the vision is in your mind’s eye).\nThe spell cannot be used to scry across planes of existence; it is limited to locations in the same plane in which it is cast.","notes":"Clairvoyance, together with clairaudience, is one of the classic “scrying” spells—spells that allow the caster to extend his or her perception and senses far into the distance to spy upon enemies and scout locations. Clairvoyance is a means of seeing (but not hearing) events in a distant location. There is no effective limit to the spell’s range, but the location must either be familiar to you (you have been there before) or be obvious, such as the top floor inside a tower you can see, or just beyond a dungeon door.\nDetails:\nThe spell cannot penetrate metal; sheets of any type of metal between the caster and the target area will prevent the magic-user from being able to scry upon the area. If the area is dark, you can see in a 10-ft. radius of the spell’s focal point as if the area were illuminated. Infravision does not boost the spell because you are not seeing with your physical eyes.\nIf the area is not dark, you can see as if you were standing at the spell’s focal point, for a normal distance but in all directions at once (the vision is in your mind’s eye).\nThe spell cannot be used to scry across planes of existence; it is limited to locations in the same plane in which it is cast.","link":""},"dispel magic":{"name":"Dispel Magic","level":"3","school":"Range: 120 ft.","range":"","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"30-ft. cube","components":"V, S","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"When you cast this spell, magical effects in the area of effect are removed or suppressed. The target point for the spell’s effect centre may be a creature, object, place, or point in space within the spell’s range.\nDetails:\nGods, demigods, artifacts, relics, and other things of equivalent power aren’t affected by this spell. Psychic or psionic powers aren’t magical effects and aren’t affected by this spell.\nWhen you finish casting this spell, if the area of effect contains any ongoing magical effects caused by a spell that you personally have cast, then these end. If a creature within the area of effect is casting a spell, then that spell is interrupted.\nThen, for each dispellable magical effect within the affected area, the GM rolls a d100—in secret, if the GM so wishes. Your base chance of successfully dispelling each effect depends on caster level, both yours and that of the caster of the magic to be dispelled. Your caster level is the number of levels you have in the magic-user class. The target’s caster level is the number of levels the caster has in the class they used to cast the spell. If the target is a potion or scroll, then its caster level is 12, unless it couldn’t have been created by a 12th-level caster, in which case its caster level is the minimum level to create it. Example: a scroll of Time Stop is caster level 18.\n    If your caster level is the same as or higher than the target’s caster level, then your chance of success is 50%, plus 5% (five percent) for each level of the difference.\n    If your caster level is lower than the target’s caster level, then your chance of success is 50%, minus 2% (two percent) for each level of the difference.\nFor each magical effect that’s dispelled:\nSpells whose area of effect is wholly within the dispel magic’s area of effect end. This includes innate spell-like powers used by creatures or cast from magic items. If a spell effect is only partly overlapped by the dispel magic, then the spell doesn’t end, but the part within the dispel magic’s area of effect is suppressed for 1 hour.\nPotions and scrolls are denatured. Potions become inert, harmless liquids. Scrolls become blank pages.\nOther magic items’ powers (weapons, armour, and other such permanent magic items) are suppressed for 1 round. For that round only, they become non-magical items.\nConstructs, elementals, golems, or magically summoned creatures within the area of effect aren’t banished or suppressed, but they could temporarily lose the power to use spells or innate spell-like powers. Example: a fire elemental’s burning touch would still do fire damage, but an efreet couldn’t use its spells or spell-like powers. Affected spells or spell-like powers return after 1d6 combat rounds.","notes":"When you cast this spell, magical effects in the area of effect are removed or suppressed. The target point for the spell’s effect centre may be a creature, object, place, or point in space within the spell’s range.\nDetails:\nGods, demigods, artifacts, relics, and other things of equivalent power aren’t affected by this spell. Psychic or psionic powers aren’t magical effects and aren’t affected by this spell.\nWhen you finish casting this spell, if the area of effect contains any ongoing magical effects caused by a spell that you personally have cast, then these end. If a creature within the area of effect is casting a spell, then that spell is interrupted.\nThen, for each dispellable magical effect within the affected area, the GM rolls a d100—in secret, if the GM so wishes. Your base chance of successfully dispelling each effect depends on caster level, both yours and that of the caster of the magic to be dispelled. Your caster level is the number of levels you have in the magic-user class. The target’s caster level is the number of levels the caster has in the class they used to cast the spell. If the target is a potion or scroll, then its caster level is 12, unless it couldn’t have been created by a 12th-level caster, in which case its caster level is the minimum level to create it. Example: a scroll of Time Stop is caster level 18.\n    If your caster level is the same as or higher than the target’s caster level, then your chance of success is 50%, plus 5% (five percent) for each level of the difference.\n    If your caster level is lower than the target’s caster level, then your chance of success is 50%, minus 2% (two percent) for each level of the difference.\nFor each magical effect that’s dispelled:\nSpells whose area of effect is wholly within the dispel magic’s area of effect end. This includes innate spell-like powers used by creatures or cast from magic items. If a spell effect is only partly overlapped by the dispel magic, then the spell doesn’t end, but the part within the dispel magic’s area of effect is suppressed for 1 hour.\nPotions and scrolls are denatured. Potions become inert, harmless liquids. Scrolls become blank pages.\nOther magic items’ powers (weapons, armour, and other such permanent magic items) are suppressed for 1 round. For that round only, they become non-magical items.\nConstructs, elementals, golems, or magically summoned creatures within the area of effect aren’t banished or suppressed, but they could temporarily lose the power to use spells or innate spell-like powers. Example: a fire elemental’s burning touch would still do fire damage, but an efreet couldn’t use its spells or spell-like powers. Affected spells or spell-like powers return after 1d6 combat rounds.","link":""},"explosive runes":{"name":"Explosive Runes","level":"3","school":"Range: Touch","range":"","duration":"Permanent until triggered","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"3 segments","save":"See below","save_type":"","description":"This spell creates a magical trap in the form of traceries and sigils placed upon a piece of writing that create a magical detonation when they are read. You and any other magic-user with whom you share the secret pattern of the runes can read the protected document or book without danger.\nDetails:\nWhen the runes are read, the resulting explosion causes 6d4+6 points of fire damage (half with a successful saving throw) to any creature within a 10-ft. radius. The reader of the runes does not receive a saving throw.\nIt is possible to detect the presence of explosive runes without detonating them: a magic-user has a 5% chance per level to notice their presence, and a thief has a 1% chance per level.\nYou can erase the runes at will. Otherwise, only a dispel magic or similar enchantment will remove the runes before they are triggered. Note that the item upon which the runes are scribed, if it is not resistant to fire, will undoubtedly be destroyed when the runes detonate.","notes":"This spell creates a magical trap in the form of traceries and sigils placed upon a piece of writing that create a magical detonation when they are read. You and any other magic-user with whom you share the secret pattern of the runes can read the protected document or book without danger.\nDetails:\nWhen the runes are read, the resulting explosion causes 6d4+6 points of fire damage (half with a successful saving throw) to any creature within a 10-ft. radius. The reader of the runes does not receive a saving throw.\nIt is possible to detect the presence of explosive runes without detonating them: a magic-user has a 5% chance per level to notice their presence, and a thief has a 1% chance per level.\nYou can erase the runes at will. Otherwise, only a dispel magic or similar enchantment will remove the runes before they are triggered. Note that the item upon which the runes are scribed, if it is not resistant to fire, will undoubtedly be destroyed when the runes detonate.","link":""},"feign death":{"name":"Feign Death","level":"3","school":"Range: Touch","range":"","duration":"6 rounds + 1 round/magic-user level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S","ct":"Fast","save":"None; willing recipient only","save_type":"","description":"This spell magically slows the recipient’s metabolism. It is impossible to tell that they aren’t actually dead.\nDetails:\nThe recipient can hear, smell, and think, but the senses of touch and sight no longer function. Damage caused to the pseudo-corpse is reduced by one half, and the spell’s recipient will not even know that the damage has been caused—potentially a dangerous situation.\nA person under the influence of this spell is not subject to level draining by the undead and will not be affected by poisons until the spell wears off or is otherwise removed. You can remove the catalepsy at will, and the spell is subject to being dispelled.","notes":"This spell magically slows the recipient’s metabolism. It is impossible to tell that they aren’t actually dead.\nDetails:\nThe recipient can hear, smell, and think, but the senses of touch and sight no longer function. Damage caused to the pseudo-corpse is reduced by one half, and the spell’s recipient will not even know that the damage has been caused—potentially a dangerous situation.\nA person under the influence of this spell is not subject to level draining by the undead and will not be affected by poisons until the spell wears off or is otherwise removed. You can remove the catalepsy at will, and the spell is subject to being dispelled.","link":""},"fireball":{"name":"Fireball","level":"3","school":"Range: 100 ft. + 10 ft./magic-user level","range":"","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Volume of a 20-ft. radius sphere (see below)","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"Yes (half damage)","save_type":"","description":"This spell creates a massive explosion of magical fire at the targeted point. The fireball detonates with a low roar, causing 1d6 points of fire damage per caster’s magic-user level to all creatures within the area of effect. Creatures making successful saving throws suffer only half the indicated damage.\nDetails:\nWhen you cast the spell, a bead of light streaks from your pointed finger to the target area, and if it strikes another object directly in its path the fireball will detonate immediately.\nThe blast fills the entire volume of the spell radius, and if it is cast into an enclosed area smaller than the area of effect the flames will expand from this area until the spell’s full volume has been reached.\nThe volume of a 20-ft. radius sphere is approximately 33,500 cubic ft., and there are 1,000 cubic ft. in a 10-ft. × 10-ft. × 10-ft. area, so in an area with a 10-ft. ceiling the fireball will fill approximately thirty-three 10-ft. × 10-ft. squares. If a fireball explodes in the middle of a corridor 10 ft. wide and 10 ft. high, the blast will extend a staggering 165 ft. in both directions. It is quite possible, particularly in dungeoneering environments, for you to be caught in the backblast of your own fireball spell.\nThe flames do not create any significant change in air pressure, but the furnace-like heat causes all items in the blast area to make saving throws against magical fire or ignite (or, in the case of metals, melt).","notes":"This spell creates a massive explosion of magical fire at the targeted point. The fireball detonates with a low roar, causing 1d6 points of fire damage per caster’s magic-user level to all creatures within the area of effect. Creatures making successful saving throws suffer only half the indicated damage.\nDetails:\nWhen you cast the spell, a bead of light streaks from your pointed finger to the target area, and if it strikes another object directly in its path the fireball will detonate immediately.\nThe blast fills the entire volume of the spell radius, and if it is cast into an enclosed area smaller than the area of effect the flames will expand from this area until the spell’s full volume has been reached.\nThe volume of a 20-ft. radius sphere is approximately 33,500 cubic ft., and there are 1,000 cubic ft. in a 10-ft. × 10-ft. × 10-ft. area, so in an area with a 10-ft. ceiling the fireball will fill approximately thirty-three 10-ft. × 10-ft. squares. If a fireball explodes in the middle of a corridor 10 ft. wide and 10 ft. high, the blast will extend a staggering 165 ft. in both directions. It is quite possible, particularly in dungeoneering environments, for you to be caught in the backblast of your own fireball spell.\nThe flames do not create any significant change in air pressure, but the furnace-like heat causes all items in the blast area to make saving throws against magical fire or ignite (or, in the case of metals, melt).","link":""},"flame arrow":{"name":"Flame Arrow","level":"3","school":"Range: Touch","range":"","duration":"1 segment/magic-user level","aoe":"Arrows or bolts","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"By means of this spell, you can enchant one arrow per segment, causing it to burst into normal flame. Each arrow causes 1 hp of fire damage in addition to its normal damage. The arrows (or crossbow bolts) will burn up in one round, so they must be shot before this time.\nDetails:\nThe enchanted arrows have no bonus to hit, but the enchantment allows them to hit a creature that can be damaged only by +1 magical weapons, even if the target creature is also immune to fire. Against creatures immune to non-magical weapons, the arrow inflicts its full piercing damage, not just the fire damage.","notes":"By means of this spell, you can enchant one arrow per segment, causing it to burst into normal flame. Each arrow causes 1 hp of fire damage in addition to its normal damage. The arrows (or crossbow bolts) will burn up in one round, so they must be shot before this time.\nDetails:\nThe enchanted arrows have no bonus to hit, but the enchantment allows them to hit a creature that can be damaged only by +1 magical weapons, even if the target creature is also immune to fire. Against creatures immune to non-magical weapons, the arrow inflicts its full piercing damage, not just the fire damage.","link":""},"fly":{"name":"Fly","level":"3","school":"Range: Touch","range":"","duration":"6 turns/magic-user level + 1d6 turns","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"This spell grants the power of flight with aerial agility level V to one creature you touch (including yourself).\nDetails:\nThe base movement rate for flight is 120 ft. per round, with the base speed being doubled when diving, halved when climbing. The GM secretly rolls a 1d6 to determine how much time the spell will last after the base 6 turns/level duration expires. Since it’s a secret roll, you don’t know exactly how long the spell will last. Be careful!","notes":"This spell grants the power of flight with aerial agility level V to one creature you touch (including yourself).\nDetails:\nThe base movement rate for flight is 120 ft. per round, with the base speed being doubled when diving, halved when climbing. The GM secretly rolls a 1d6 to determine how much time the spell will last after the base 6 turns/level duration expires. Since it’s a secret roll, you don’t know exactly how long the spell will last. Be careful!","link":""},"gust of wind":{"name":"Gust of Wind","level":"3","school":"Range: Nil","range":"","duration":"1 segment","aoe":"10-ft. wide path, 10 ft. long/magic-user level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Hand outstretched in the final somatic gesture of this spell, you summon forth a powerful blast of air, forceful enough to blow out unprotected flames smaller than a campfire.\nDetails:\nShielded small flames have a high chance of being extinguished (5% per caster level). Large flames (campfire or greater) are not extinguished but will flare back as far as 1d6 feet. The wind is strong enough to hurl a tiny or small flying creature backwards by 1d6×10 ft. Medium-sized flying creatures cannot move forward into the wind, but can hold their place. Larger creatures are not affected.","notes":"Hand outstretched in the final somatic gesture of this spell, you summon forth a powerful blast of air, forceful enough to blow out unprotected flames smaller than a campfire.\nDetails:\nShielded small flames have a high chance of being extinguished (5% per caster level). Large flames (campfire or greater) are not extinguished but will flare back as far as 1d6 feet. The wind is strong enough to hurl a tiny or small flying creature backwards by 1d6×10 ft. Medium-sized flying creatures cannot move forward into the wind, but can hold their place. Larger creatures are not affected.","link":""},"haste":{"name":"Haste","level":"3","school":"Range: 60 ft.","range":"","duration":"3 rounds + 1 round/magic-user level","aoe":"1 creature/magic-user level in a 40-ft. × 40-ft. area","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None (willing targets only)","save_type":"","description":"This spell allows creatures in the targeted area to move with preternatural speed, moving and attacking at twice the normal rate. The rate of spell casting cannot be increased, only movement and attack.\nDetails:\nWithin the area of effect, creatures closest to you are affected first if your level is not high enough to affect all creatures in the area. This spell ages the creatures on which it is cast by 2 years, which is a major disadvantage.","notes":"This spell allows creatures in the targeted area to move with preternatural speed, moving and attacking at twice the normal rate. The rate of spell casting cannot be increased, only movement and attack.\nDetails:\nWithin the area of effect, creatures closest to you are affected first if your level is not high enough to affect all creatures in the area. This spell ages the creatures on which it is cast by 2 years, which is a major disadvantage.","link":""},"hold person":{"name":"Hold Person","level":"3","school":"Range: 120 ft.","range":"","duration":"2 rounds/magic-user level","aoe":"Up to 4 creatures of your choice within range","components":"V","ct":"3 segments","save":"Yes (see below)","save_type":"","description":"The selected creatures must make a saving throw against spells or be paralysed for the spell’s duration. The difficulty of the saving throw depends on the number of creatures targeted (see below).\nDetails:\nCreatures aren’t affected if they are not bipedal (human, demi-human, or humanoid-like) and size Medium or smaller. An affected creature is allowed a saving throw vs. spells. The target creature applies its Wisdom save modifier, if it has one, to this saving throw. There’s a further modifier that depends on how many creatures you chose to affect:\n    If you chose to affect only one creature, it saves at -3.\n    If you chose to affect two creatures, they save at -1.\n    If you chose to affect three or four creatures, each makes the saving throw with no penalty.\nCombat Effects:\nThis is a reminder about the rules applicable to paralyzed creatures, so the word “you” applies to everyone, not just to the caster of the spell. Held creatures are physically helpless. If you’re holding a hand weapon and not in melee, then you can use your hand weapon to automatically kill one held creature each round. If you’re not in melee and you’re holding a rope, chain, or other means of binding, then instead of attacking, you can bind one held creature each round.\nIn some cases (if you are still in melee with others, have multiple attacks, or if your objective is to cast a touch spell) you might choose to make normal attacks rather than the automatic kill approach. If you attack a held creature with a weapon attack, unarmed attack, or touch spell, then you always hit it unless you choose to miss. When you hit it with a weapon attack or unarmed attack, you can choose to inflict the maximum possible damage instead of rolling it, and if every creature you’re attacking is held, then your number of attacks this round is doubled.","notes":"The selected creatures must make a saving throw against spells or be paralysed for the spell’s duration. The difficulty of the saving throw depends on the number of creatures targeted (see below).\nDetails:\nCreatures aren’t affected if they are not bipedal (human, demi-human, or humanoid-like) and size Medium or smaller. An affected creature is allowed a saving throw vs. spells. The target creature applies its Wisdom save modifier, if it has one, to this saving throw. There’s a further modifier that depends on how many creatures you chose to affect:\n    If you chose to affect only one creature, it saves at -3.\n    If you chose to affect two creatures, they save at -1.\n    If you chose to affect three or four creatures, each makes the saving throw with no penalty.\nCombat Effects:\nThis is a reminder about the rules applicable to paralyzed creatures, so the word “you” applies to everyone, not just to the caster of the spell. Held creatures are physically helpless. If you’re holding a hand weapon and not in melee, then you can use your hand weapon to automatically kill one held creature each round. If you’re not in melee and you’re holding a rope, chain, or other means of binding, then instead of attacking, you can bind one held creature each round.\nIn some cases (if you are still in melee with others, have multiple attacks, or if your objective is to cast a touch spell) you might choose to make normal attacks rather than the automatic kill approach. If you attack a held creature with a weapon attack, unarmed attack, or touch spell, then you always hit it unless you choose to miss. When you hit it with a weapon attack or unarmed attack, you can choose to inflict the maximum possible damage instead of rolling it, and if every creature you’re attacking is held, then your number of attacks this round is doubled.","link":""},"infravision":{"name":"Infravision","level":"3","school":"Range: Touch","range":"Touch","duration":"See below","aoe":"All creatures within a 10-ft. radius","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None (willing target only)","save_type":"","description":"This spell grants you or a creature you touch with the ability to see in the dark, perceiving variations of heat in the infrared spectrum. The range of this vision is 60 ft.\nDetails:\nLamps and other light sources tend to spoil the effects of infravision. Note: Infravision does not allow you to detect invisibility.\nINVISIBILITY, 10-FT. RADIUS\nArcane Illusion, Level 3\nThis spell operates as does the invisibility spell, but affects all willing creatures within 10 ft. of the touched creature at the time the final words of the spell are uttered. As the caster, you can remain visible, if you choose, by being an “unwilling subject”.\nDetails:\nIf the creature upon which the spell was cast makes an attack (including casting a spell that directly causes damage, such as a fireball), the attack negates the invisibility of all the others. However, if one of the creatures affected by the spell’s radius (not the direct recipient) attacks, the invisibility only of that one creature is negated thereby.\nIn order to remain invisible, those who were made invisible by virtue of the spell’s radius must remain within 10 ft. of the creature upon whom the spell is centred. All creatures affected can see each other. Note that the spell does not make the recipient any more quiet than normal, nor does it eliminate scents.","notes":"This spell grants you or a creature you touch with the ability to see in the dark, perceiving variations of heat in the infrared spectrum. The range of this vision is 60 ft.\nDetails:\nLamps and other light sources tend to spoil the effects of infravision. Note: Infravision does not allow you to detect invisibility.\nINVISIBILITY, 10-FT. RADIUS\nArcane Illusion, Level 3\nThis spell operates as does the invisibility spell, but affects all willing creatures within 10 ft. of the touched creature at the time the final words of the spell are uttered. As the caster, you can remain visible, if you choose, by being an “unwilling subject”.\nDetails:\nIf the creature upon which the spell was cast makes an attack (including casting a spell that directly causes damage, such as a fireball), the attack negates the invisibility of all the others. However, if one of the creatures affected by the spell’s radius (not the direct recipient) attacks, the invisibility only of that one creature is negated thereby.\nIn order to remain invisible, those who were made invisible by virtue of the spell’s radius must remain within 10 ft. of the creature upon whom the spell is centred. All creatures affected can see each other. Note that the spell does not make the recipient any more quiet than normal, nor does it eliminate scents.","link":""},"leomund s tiny hut":{"name":"Leomund’S Tiny Hut","level":"3","school":"Range: Nil","range":"","duration":"6 turns/magic-user level","aoe":"5-ft. radius sphere","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"This spell causes a bubble of magical force to form around you, providing protection from the elements for you and anyone who can fit into the protected area.\nDetails:\nThe field extends through solid substances if necessary, providing a complete sphere of protection. When you cast it on the ground, the sphere will thus appear to be a hemisphere, with half of it beneath the ground. The field’s outside surface is not transparent and is usually a dark amber colour, but anyone inside the sphere can see through to the outside as if the force field did not exist.\nThe spell provides protection against inclement winds and temperature within a certain range, but offers no protection against attacks from outside. Anyone can pass into and out of the hut, and up to 6 medium-sized or 8 small creatures can shelter inside with you. If you leave the hut, the spell ends.\nInside the hut, the inhabitants will not feel winds of up to 50 mph, which are completely blocked by the bubble of force, but if the wind reaches gale force of 50 mph the tiny hut will be shredded into oblivion. The temperature inside the hut remains at a pleasant 70° Fahrenheit for so long as the outside temperature remains in a range from 0° to 100°. For every degree of outside temperature beyond this range, the temperature inside the hut will rise or fall accordingly from 70°. You may illuminate the inside of the hut with a dim, ambient light that will not, of course, show to the outside.","notes":"This spell causes a bubble of magical force to form around you, providing protection from the elements for you and anyone who can fit into the protected area.\nDetails:\nThe field extends through solid substances if necessary, providing a complete sphere of protection. When you cast it on the ground, the sphere will thus appear to be a hemisphere, with half of it beneath the ground. The field’s outside surface is not transparent and is usually a dark amber colour, but anyone inside the sphere can see through to the outside as if the force field did not exist.\nThe spell provides protection against inclement winds and temperature within a certain range, but offers no protection against attacks from outside. Anyone can pass into and out of the hut, and up to 6 medium-sized or 8 small creatures can shelter inside with you. If you leave the hut, the spell ends.\nInside the hut, the inhabitants will not feel winds of up to 50 mph, which are completely blocked by the bubble of force, but if the wind reaches gale force of 50 mph the tiny hut will be shredded into oblivion. The temperature inside the hut remains at a pleasant 70° Fahrenheit for so long as the outside temperature remains in a range from 0° to 100°. For every degree of outside temperature beyond this range, the temperature inside the hut will rise or fall accordingly from 70°. You may illuminate the inside of the hut with a dim, ambient light that will not, of course, show to the outside.","link":""},"lightning bolt":{"name":"Lightning Bolt","level":"3","school":"Range: 40 ft. + 10 ft./magic-user level","range":"","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"See below","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"Yes (half damage)","save_type":"","description":"You unleash a bolt of lightning from the spell’s point of origin, which may be as far away from you as the spell’s maximum range. The direction of the bolt follows the line from you to the origin point. Even though the bolt starts at the origin point, it still follows a line directly away from you. The bolt itself (the area of effect) may extend beyond the spell’s range.\nDetails:\nThe bolt deals 1d6 points of electrical damage per magic-user level to all creatures standing in the bolt’s area of effect (see below). Creatures that make successful saving throws suffer half damage.\nAt your option, the area of effect may be either a branching, forking maelstrom of electricity 10 ft. wide and 40 ft. long, or it may be a concentrated blast 5 ft. wide and 80 ft. long. The length of the bolt itself is not affected by your level, only the range at which you may cause the bolt to originate.\nFree-standing items and items held or worn by a creature who fails the saving throw must make an item saving throw vs. lightning or be destroyed.\nIf the bolt strikes an object that does not conduct electricity, such as a stone wall, it will be deflected backward toward the caster (potentially inflicting a second shock upon those in the target area). The length of a deflected bolt is not increased; the bolt only rebounds for the distance remaining in its original area of effect.","notes":"You unleash a bolt of lightning from the spell’s point of origin, which may be as far away from you as the spell’s maximum range. The direction of the bolt follows the line from you to the origin point. Even though the bolt starts at the origin point, it still follows a line directly away from you. The bolt itself (the area of effect) may extend beyond the spell’s range.\nDetails:\nThe bolt deals 1d6 points of electrical damage per magic-user level to all creatures standing in the bolt’s area of effect (see below). Creatures that make successful saving throws suffer half damage.\nAt your option, the area of effect may be either a branching, forking maelstrom of electricity 10 ft. wide and 40 ft. long, or it may be a concentrated blast 5 ft. wide and 80 ft. long. The length of the bolt itself is not affected by your level, only the range at which you may cause the bolt to originate.\nFree-standing items and items held or worn by a creature who fails the saving throw must make an item saving throw vs. lightning or be destroyed.\nIf the bolt strikes an object that does not conduct electricity, such as a stone wall, it will be deflected backward toward the caster (potentially inflicting a second shock upon those in the target area). The length of a deflected bolt is not increased; the bolt only rebounds for the distance remaining in its original area of effect.","link":""},"monster summoning i":{"name":"Monster Summoning I","level":"3","school":"Range: 30 ft.","range":"","duration":"2 rounds + 1 round/magic-user level","aoe":"Summoned creatures","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"By casting this spell, you conjure up 2d4 monsters to serve you as allies in combat or to perform other services. Technically, this spell is a conjuration: the monsters appear from thin air within 1d4 rounds of the spell’s completed casting.\nDetails:\nIf you are in combat, the monsters will fight on your behalf, attacking whatever foes you direct, or guarding you. For more complex tasks, you must somehow have the ability to communicate these more specific commands.\nThe GM has the ultimate discretion as to what monsters will appear, but the general likelihood is described in the following table:\nMonster Summoning I Results (Magic-User Level 3)\nd6 — Monster Summoned\n1 — Rat, giant\n2 — Goblin\n3 — Hobgoblin\n4 — Kobold\n5 — Orc\n6 — Demon, manes","notes":"By casting this spell, you conjure up 2d4 monsters to serve you as allies in combat or to perform other services. Technically, this spell is a conjuration: the monsters appear from thin air within 1d4 rounds of the spell’s completed casting.\nDetails:\nIf you are in combat, the monsters will fight on your behalf, attacking whatever foes you direct, or guarding you. For more complex tasks, you must somehow have the ability to communicate these more specific commands.\nThe GM has the ultimate discretion as to what monsters will appear, but the general likelihood is described in the following table:\nMonster Summoning I Results (Magic-User Level 3)\nd6 — Monster Summoned\n1 — Rat, giant\n2 — Goblin\n3 — Hobgoblin\n4 — Kobold\n5 — Orc\n6 — Demon, manes","link":""},"phantasmal force":{"name":"Phantasmal Force","level":"3","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"80 ft. + 10 ft./magic-user level","duration":"See below","aoe":"80 sq. ft. + 10 sq. ft./magic-user level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"See below","save_type":"","description":"This extremely flexible spell allows you to craft a visual illusion of virtually anything that can fit within the spell’s area of effect. The spell creates no sound whatsoever. You must maintain your concentration upon the illusion, or it will evaporate, but while concentrating you are able to make the illusion move and respond to events. The illusion is dispelled if it is struck with a blow, a falling person, etc.\nDetails:\nThere is no saving throw against the illusion if the observer believes it, and the illusion can actually cause damage to such a deceived victim. A demon wielding a sword can attack and do damage, and the appearance of a pit full of spikes can be fatal even though it is not real.\nIf the observer doubts the reality of the illusion, they are permitted a saving throw to see the illusion for what it really is. If one observer disbelieves the illusion and this disbelief is communicated to others, the others will also gain a saving throw at a bonus of +4.\nNote that the spell relies purely on a visual effect; it will have no effect upon a creature that does not see it. Furthermore, the lack of any audible component can make certain illusions completely non-credible. An explosion, for example, is not likely to be believed by anyone if it creates no sound.\nVarious methods may be used by the GM to determine if an NPC or monster believes the effect of a phantasmal force, common sense being the first thing to consider. A player who takes care to craft a believable illusion should be rewarded for skilful use of the spell, not forced into a table of random results.","notes":"This extremely flexible spell allows you to craft a visual illusion of virtually anything that can fit within the spell’s area of effect. The spell creates no sound whatsoever. You must maintain your concentration upon the illusion, or it will evaporate, but while concentrating you are able to make the illusion move and respond to events. The illusion is dispelled if it is struck with a blow, a falling person, etc.\nDetails:\nThere is no saving throw against the illusion if the observer believes it, and the illusion can actually cause damage to such a deceived victim. A demon wielding a sword can attack and do damage, and the appearance of a pit full of spikes can be fatal even though it is not real.\nIf the observer doubts the reality of the illusion, they are permitted a saving throw to see the illusion for what it really is. If one observer disbelieves the illusion and this disbelief is communicated to others, the others will also gain a saving throw at a bonus of +4.\nNote that the spell relies purely on a visual effect; it will have no effect upon a creature that does not see it. Furthermore, the lack of any audible component can make certain illusions completely non-credible. An explosion, for example, is not likely to be believed by anyone if it creates no sound.\nVarious methods may be used by the GM to determine if an NPC or monster believes the effect of a phantasmal force, common sense being the first thing to consider. A player who takes care to craft a believable illusion should be rewarded for skilful use of the spell, not forced into a table of random results.","link":""},"protection from normal missiles":{"name":"Protection From Normal Missiles","level":"3","school":"Abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 turn/magic-user level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"The target of this spell is protected from missile weapons.\nDetails:\nThe spell completely protects the subject from non-magical arrows, bolts, thrown weapons, and similar projectiles. Larger missiles hurled by siege engines such as catapults and ballistae, and magical arrows or bolts, have their damage reduced by 1 hit point per die.\nThe spell conveys no protection whatsoever against spells, including spells with missile-like qualities such as fireball or ray of enfeeblement.","notes":"The target of this spell is protected from missile weapons.\nDetails:\nThe spell completely protects the subject from non-magical arrows, bolts, thrown weapons, and similar projectiles. Larger missiles hurled by siege engines such as catapults and ballistae, and magical arrows or bolts, have their damage reduced by 1 hit point per die.\nThe spell conveys no protection whatsoever against spells, including spells with missile-like qualities such as fireball or ray of enfeeblement.","link":""},"slow":{"name":"Slow","level":"3","school":"Transmutation/Alteration","range":"90 ft. + 10 ft./magic-user level","duration":"3 rounds + 1 round/magic-user level","aoe":"1 creature/magic-user level in a 40-ft. × 40-ft. area","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"This spell acts upon its targets to slow down their movements, and it can be used to negate the effects of a haste spell.\nDetails:\nA creature affected by a slow spell can only move at half normal speed and attack at half its normal rate.\nThe spell may be cast upon up to 1 creature/caster level, but all must be within the spell’s area of effect at the time of casting. If more than one slow spell is cast upon the same subject, the effects of the two spells will be cumulative.","notes":"This spell acts upon its targets to slow down their movements, and it can be used to negate the effects of a haste spell.\nDetails:\nA creature affected by a slow spell can only move at half normal speed and attack at half its normal rate.\nThe spell may be cast upon up to 1 creature/caster level, but all must be within the spell’s area of effect at the time of casting. If more than one slow spell is cast upon the same subject, the effects of the two spells will be cumulative.","link":""},"suggestion":{"name":"Suggestion","level":"3","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"30 ft.","duration":"6 turns + 6 turns/magic-user level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"Negates effect","save_type":"","description":"This spell allows you to make a factual suggestion or suggest a course of action to the target creature. If the creature fails a saving throw, it adopts and follows the suggestion.\nDetails:\nThe suggestion must be made as soon as the casting time is completed; duration applies to the length of time the creature follows the suggestion.\nYou can make a factual suggestion (“These are not the halflings you seek”), suggest a course of action (“Don’t mention you saw us”), or make a combination of both. Even a victim who has failed a saving throw against the spell will not undertake a course of action that is unreasonable, but the experienced caster can easily phrase his or her requests in such a way as to avoid this problem.\nExample: No creature will leap off a cliff for no reason; but the caster might “need to scout the bottom of a chasm” and promise to cast a feather fall spell, or hand the victim a “magical” torch that supposedly permits the power of flight.\nThe creature to be influenced must be able to hear and understand the language spoken by the caster.","notes":"This spell allows you to make a factual suggestion or suggest a course of action to the target creature. If the creature fails a saving throw, it adopts and follows the suggestion.\nDetails:\nThe suggestion must be made as soon as the casting time is completed; duration applies to the length of time the creature follows the suggestion.\nYou can make a factual suggestion (“These are not the halflings you seek”), suggest a course of action (“Don’t mention you saw us”), or make a combination of both. Even a victim who has failed a saving throw against the spell will not undertake a course of action that is unreasonable, but the experienced caster can easily phrase his or her requests in such a way as to avoid this problem.\nExample: No creature will leap off a cliff for no reason; but the caster might “need to scout the bottom of a chasm” and promise to cast a feather fall spell, or hand the victim a “magical” torch that supposedly permits the power of flight.\nThe creature to be influenced must be able to hear and understand the language spoken by the caster.","link":""},"tongues":{"name":"Tongues","level":"3","school":"Transmutation/Alteration","range":"Nil","duration":"1 round/magic-user level","aoe":"30-ft. radius","components":"V, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Within the radius established by this spell, you (you only) will be able to speak and understand any verbal language, including alignment tongues.\nDetails:\nNote that the spell’s area of effect does not move with you. Only you can hear the magical translation when other creatures speak, and only if the words are spoken within the area of effect. Everyone within the area of effect can hear the magical translation of your words.\nOnly spoken words are affected. Writing, and non-verbal communication such as hand signals, are not. Creatures only understand you if they naturally speak at least one language.\nReversible as: BABBLE","notes":"Within the radius established by this spell, you (you only) will be able to speak and understand any verbal language, including alignment tongues.\nDetails:\nNote that the spell’s area of effect does not move with you. Only you can hear the magical translation when other creatures speak, and only if the words are spoken within the area of effect. Everyone within the area of effect can hear the magical translation of your words.\nOnly spoken words are affected. Writing, and non-verbal communication such as hand signals, are not. Creatures only understand you if they naturally speak at least one language.\nReversible as: BABBLE","link":""},"babble":{"name":"Babble","level":"3","school":"Transmutation/Alteration","range":"Nil","duration":"1 round/magic-user level","aoe":"30-ft. radius","components":"V, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"This spell makes any verbal communication impossible for any person (not just the caster) in the spell’s area, or it may be used to cancel out the effects of the tongues spell (whether cast by a cleric or by a magic-user).\nDetails:\nAlthough spoken words become meaningless in the area of effect, creatures can still gesture, write, and otherwise communicate. Note: Creatures in the area of effect can’t cast spells that have a verbal component until the spell ends.","notes":"This spell makes any verbal communication impossible for any person (not just the caster) in the spell’s area, or it may be used to cancel out the effects of the tongues spell (whether cast by a cleric or by a magic-user).\nDetails:\nAlthough spoken words become meaningless in the area of effect, creatures can still gesture, write, and otherwise communicate. Note: Creatures in the area of effect can’t cast spells that have a verbal component until the spell ends.","link":""},"water breathing":{"name":"Water Breathing","level":"3","school":"Transmutation/Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"3 turns/magic-user level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"This spell grants the ability to breathe underwater while the spell lasts. The recipient does not lose the ability to breathe air.\nReversible as: AIR BREATHING","notes":"This spell grants the ability to breathe underwater while the spell lasts. The recipient does not lose the ability to breathe air.\nReversible as: AIR BREATHING","link":""},"air breathing":{"name":"Air Breathing","level":"3","school":"Transmutation/Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"3 turns/magic-user level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"This spell allows a water-breathing creature to breathe air for the spell’s duration. The recipient does not lose the ability to breathe underwater.","notes":"This spell allows a water-breathing creature to breathe air for the spell’s duration. The recipient does not lose the ability to breathe underwater.","link":""},"charm monster":{"name":"Charm Monster","level":"4","school":"Range: 60 ft.","range":"","duration":"See below","aoe":"See below","components":"V, S","ct":"4 segments","save":"Negates effect","save_type":"","description":"This spell causes the target (or targets) to view you as a trusted friend, if they fail a saving throw vs. spells.\nDetails:\nThe spell only affects one hit die category (from the table below) per casting. Example: if ten orcs (<1 to 1+ HD) are in the spell’s range, along with a bugbear (3 to 3+ category), you will have to decide whether to target the orcs or the bugbear. If you chose to target the orcs, you would roll 2d4. If the result of the die roll were a 4, then 4 orcs would need to make saving throws.\nIf there are ten kobolds and an orc in range, these are all in the same hit die category (<1 to 1+). However, the weakest creature type in the category is affected first, just as the sleep spell works.\nIf the target creature fails a saving throw, it will view you as a trusted friend, interpreting your every word in its most positive light. Charmed creatures will place themselves into moderate danger, including combat, on your behalf, but will not undertake risks beyond those the creature might ordinarily take. You must be able to talk to the charmed creature if you want to make any sort of complex “request”.\nCharmed creatures are allowed periodic saving throws to break the charm, based on their hit dice:\nHit Dice of Monsters\tNumber Potentially Affected\tChance/Week to Break Enchantment\n<1 to 1+\t2d4\t5%\n2 to 2+\t1d4\t10%\n3 to 3+\t1d2\t15%\n4 to 4+\t1\t25%\n5 to 5+\t1\t35%\n6 to 6+\t1\t45%\n7 to 7+\t1\t60%\n8 to 8+\t1\t75%\n9+\t1\t90%\nThe distinction between this spell and the weaker charm person is that this spell affects any creature, not just “persons.”","notes":"This spell causes the target (or targets) to view you as a trusted friend, if they fail a saving throw vs. spells.\nDetails:\nThe spell only affects one hit die category (from the table below) per casting. Example: if ten orcs (<1 to 1+ HD) are in the spell’s range, along with a bugbear (3 to 3+ category), you will have to decide whether to target the orcs or the bugbear. If you chose to target the orcs, you would roll 2d4. If the result of the die roll were a 4, then 4 orcs would need to make saving throws.\nIf there are ten kobolds and an orc in range, these are all in the same hit die category (<1 to 1+). However, the weakest creature type in the category is affected first, just as the sleep spell works.\nIf the target creature fails a saving throw, it will view you as a trusted friend, interpreting your every word in its most positive light. Charmed creatures will place themselves into moderate danger, including combat, on your behalf, but will not undertake risks beyond those the creature might ordinarily take. You must be able to talk to the charmed creature if you want to make any sort of complex “request”.\nCharmed creatures are allowed periodic saving throws to break the charm, based on their hit dice:\nHit Dice of Monsters\tNumber Potentially Affected\tChance/Week to Break Enchantment\n<1 to 1+\t2d4\t5%\n2 to 2+\t1d4\t10%\n3 to 3+\t1d2\t15%\n4 to 4+\t1\t25%\n5 to 5+\t1\t35%\n6 to 6+\t1\t45%\n7 to 7+\t1\t60%\n8 to 8+\t1\t75%\n9+\t1\t90%\nThe distinction between this spell and the weaker charm person is that this spell affects any creature, not just “persons.”","link":""},"confusion":{"name":"Confusion","level":"4","school":"Range: 120 ft.","range":"","duration":"2 rounds + 1 round/magic-user level","aoe":"Up to 60 ft. × 60 ft.","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"See below","save_type":"","description":"This spell causes creatures to behave strangely and unpredictably. A certain number of creatures in the spell’s area of effect when the spell is cast must make a saving throw each round in order to avoid becoming confused. The effect persists after they leave the area of effect until the spell’s duration expires.\nDetails:\nThe base number of creatures affected by the spell is 2d8, but additional creatures may be affected. Take the hit dice of the strongest creature in the area of effect and compare it to your magic-user level. If your magic-user level is higher by any number, add that number to the base 2d8; if it is lower, subtract it. The result is the maximum number of creatures in the area of effect that must make a saving throw. If there are more creatures in the area than this, the ones closest to the caster are affected first.\nAll saving throws are made with a penalty of -2. A saving throw is made for each creature each round unless they “meander away,” which continues for a full turn but probably takes them out of the area of effect during that time. A creature that succeeds at the saving throw but stays in the area of effect must continue to make saving throws each round until the spell ends.\nCreatures that fail their saving throws act randomly. Roll 1d100 for each creature:\nd100 — Effect\n01–10 — Attacks you or your allies (but not with spells)\n11–20 — Acts normally\n21–50 — Babbles incoherently and takes no action\n51–70 — Meanders away from you for a full turn at normal speed\n71–00 — Attacks nearest creature regardless of allegiance","notes":"This spell causes creatures to behave strangely and unpredictably. A certain number of creatures in the spell’s area of effect when the spell is cast must make a saving throw each round in order to avoid becoming confused. The effect persists after they leave the area of effect until the spell’s duration expires.\nDetails:\nThe base number of creatures affected by the spell is 2d8, but additional creatures may be affected. Take the hit dice of the strongest creature in the area of effect and compare it to your magic-user level. If your magic-user level is higher by any number, add that number to the base 2d8; if it is lower, subtract it. The result is the maximum number of creatures in the area of effect that must make a saving throw. If there are more creatures in the area than this, the ones closest to the caster are affected first.\nAll saving throws are made with a penalty of -2. A saving throw is made for each creature each round unless they “meander away,” which continues for a full turn but probably takes them out of the area of effect during that time. A creature that succeeds at the saving throw but stays in the area of effect must continue to make saving throws each round until the spell ends.\nCreatures that fail their saving throws act randomly. Roll 1d100 for each creature:\nd100 — Effect\n01–10 — Attacks you or your allies (but not with spells)\n11–20 — Acts normally\n21–50 — Babbles incoherently and takes no action\n51–70 — Meanders away from you for a full turn at normal speed\n71–00 — Attacks nearest creature regardless of allegiance","link":""},"dig":{"name":"Dig","level":"4","school":"Range: 30 ft.","range":"","duration":"1 round/magic-user level","aoe":"5-ft. cube/magic-user level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"See below","save_type":"","description":"This spell causes dirt to begin piling out from the ground, digging a hole with tremendous speed. The excavation proceeds at a rate of one 5-ft. × 5-ft. cube per round, as earth boils out of the area you indicate, landing at the edges of the pit.\nDetails:\nIf the spell is cast directly beneath a creature, the creature will fall in without any possibility of a saving throw. Creatures at the edge of the pit have some likelihood of falling in; they must roll lower than their Dexterity score on a d20 to avoid sliding into the sudden maelstrom of moving earth. A creature moving toward the pit during the first round in which digging begins must make a saving throw vs. spells or fall into the hole.\nThe spell can be used to excavate in dirt, sand, or mud, but not rock. Note that if the pit is taken deeper than 5 ft., there is a chance that it will collapse in on itself (roughly 25%, adjusted by the GM for the type of material being dug).","notes":"This spell causes dirt to begin piling out from the ground, digging a hole with tremendous speed. The excavation proceeds at a rate of one 5-ft. × 5-ft. cube per round, as earth boils out of the area you indicate, landing at the edges of the pit.\nDetails:\nIf the spell is cast directly beneath a creature, the creature will fall in without any possibility of a saving throw. Creatures at the edge of the pit have some likelihood of falling in; they must roll lower than their Dexterity score on a d20 to avoid sliding into the sudden maelstrom of moving earth. A creature moving toward the pit during the first round in which digging begins must make a saving throw vs. spells or fall into the hole.\nThe spell can be used to excavate in dirt, sand, or mud, but not rock. Note that if the pit is taken deeper than 5 ft., there is a chance that it will collapse in on itself (roughly 25%, adjusted by the GM for the type of material being dug).","link":""},"dimension door":{"name":"Dimension Door","level":"4","school":"Range: Caster","range":"","duration":"See below","aoe":"Caster","components":"V","ct":"Fast","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Dimension door is a weak form of teleportation, more controllable than blink, but severely limited in range. The teleportation is limited to 30 ft. per caster level.\nDetails:\nUnlike blink, a dimension door spell operates with perfect accuracy, either to a place you can see or clearly visualise, or in response to directions (example: “120 ft. forward and 30 ft. to the right”). If your directions land you inside a solid object, you are stunned and trapped in the Astral Plane, held in a sort of suspended animation for eternity unless rescued.\nThe spell is subject to a maximum weight limit of 500 lbs. of additional weight, with each pound of living matter counting for twice its actual weight. Recovery from the experience of this form of teleportation is not immediate, although it is quite rapid. You cannot act for a period of 6 combat segments following the transition.","notes":"Dimension door is a weak form of teleportation, more controllable than blink, but severely limited in range. The teleportation is limited to 30 ft. per caster level.\nDetails:\nUnlike blink, a dimension door spell operates with perfect accuracy, either to a place you can see or clearly visualise, or in response to directions (example: “120 ft. forward and 30 ft. to the right”). If your directions land you inside a solid object, you are stunned and trapped in the Astral Plane, held in a sort of suspended animation for eternity unless rescued.\nThe spell is subject to a maximum weight limit of 500 lbs. of additional weight, with each pound of living matter counting for twice its actual weight. Recovery from the experience of this form of teleportation is not immediate, although it is quite rapid. You cannot act for a period of 6 combat segments following the transition.","link":""},"enchanted weapon":{"name":"Enchanted Weapon","level":"4","school":"Range: Touch","range":"","duration":"5 rounds/magic-user level","aoe":"See below","components":"V, S, M","ct":"(not stated here)","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"With a touch of your hand, you create a weak and temporary enchantment upon a full-sized weapon, or upon two smaller weapons such as arrows, bolts, or daggers.\nDetails:\nThe enchantment lends no bonus to hit or on damage, but may be used to strike creatures that are immune to damage from non-magical weapons. If the enchanted weapon is an arrow or other type of ammunition, the enchantment ends when the weapon hits successfully. A melee weapon remains enchanted for the duration.","notes":"With a touch of your hand, you create a weak and temporary enchantment upon a full-sized weapon, or upon two smaller weapons such as arrows, bolts, or daggers.\nDetails:\nThe enchantment lends no bonus to hit or on damage, but may be used to strike creatures that are immune to damage from non-magical weapons. If the enchanted weapon is an arrow or other type of ammunition, the enchantment ends when the weapon hits successfully. A melee weapon remains enchanted for the duration.","link"