s, and saving throws.\nDetails:\n    Cumulative with chant despite similarity.", "link": ""}, "remove curse": {"name": "Remove Curse", "level": "3", "school": "Divine abjuration", "range": "Touch", "duration": "Instantaneous", "aoe": "One creature, object, or place", "components": "V, S", "ct": "6 segments", "save": "None", "save_type": "", "description": "Ends one curse on a target creature, object, or place.\nDetails:\n    Curses from gods/demigods/artifacts/relics are not affected.\n    Does not cure vampirism or lycanthropy.\n    If the target is a creature with multiple curses, you choose which curse ends.\n    If the target is a cursed object, the curse does not end, but a creature holding it is allowed to drop it and be free of it.\nReversible as Bestow Curse:", "notes": "Ends one curse on a target creature, object, or place.\nDetails:\n    Curses from gods/demigods/artifacts/relics are not affected.\n    Does not cure vampirism or lycanthropy.\n    If the target is a creature with multiple curses, you choose which curse ends.\n    If the target is a cursed object, the curse does not end, but a creature holding it is allowed to drop it and be free of it.\nReversible as Bestow Curse:", "link": ""}, "speak with dead": {"name": "Speak with Dead", "level": "3", "school": "Divine necromancy", "range": "10 ft", "duration": "Varies (see table)", "aoe": "One corpse", "components": "V, S, M", "ct": "10 rounds", "save": "None", "save_type": "", "description": "Compels a corpse to answer questions aloud (others can hear). Duration, question limit, and maximum corpse age depend on your cleric level.\nLimitations by cleric level:\nCleric Level\tDuration\tMax Questions\tMax Time Since Death\n5–6\t1 round\t2\t1 week\n7–8\t3 rounds\t3\t1 month\n9–12\t1 turn\t4\t1 year\n13–15\t2 turns\t5\t1 decade\n16–19\t3 turns\t6\t1 century\n20\t1 hour\t7\t1 aeon\nDetails:\n    The corpse can only tell what it knew in life.\n    It only speaks languages it knew in life. If it doesn’t understand a question, it can say “I don’t understand,” and this still consumes one question.\n    The spell does not make it friendly. If it was hostile (especially if you killed it), it answers briefly and with minimal information.\n    Multi-part questions get only one part answered (corpse chooses which).\n    Ambiguous questions may be interpreted in any reasonable way (GM adjudication).\n    If the target is undead, it does not have to stop fighting while answering.", "notes": "Compels a corpse to answer questions aloud (others can hear). Duration, question limit, and maximum corpse age depend on your cleric level.\nLimitations by cleric level:\nCleric Level\tDuration\tMax Questions\tMax Time Since Death\n5–6\t1 round\t2\t1 week\n7–8\t3 rounds\t3\t1 month\n9–12\t1 turn\t4\t1 year\n13–15\t2 turns\t5\t1 decade\n16–19\t3 turns\t6\t1 century\n20\t1 hour\t7\t1 aeon\nDetails:\n    The corpse can only tell what it knew in life.\n    It only speaks languages it knew in life. If it doesn’t understand a question, it can say “I don’t understand,” and this still consumes one question.\n    The spell does not make it friendly. If it was hostile (especially if you killed it), it answers briefly and with minimal information.\n    Multi-part questions get only one part answered (corpse chooses which).\n    Ambiguous questions may be interpreted in any reasonable way (GM adjudication).\n    If the target is undead, it does not have to stop fighting while answering.", "link": ""}, "blither": {"name": "Blither", "level": "4", "school": "Divine enchantment", "range": "Touch", "duration": "1 turn", "aoe": "One creature", "components": "V, S, M", "ct": "7 segments", "save": "Yes (negates effect)", "save_type": "", "description": "Noise: Casting quiet; effect quiet\nRenders a creature’s spoken words meaningless for the duration; it cannot communicate via speech.\nDetails:\n    Target may add its Wisdom saving throw modifier to the saving throw.\n    On failure, it can still gesture, write, and otherwise communicate.\n    The affected creature cannot cast spells with verbal components until the spell ends.", "notes": "Noise: Casting quiet; effect quiet\nRenders a creature’s spoken words meaningless for the duration; it cannot communicate via speech.\nDetails:\n    Target may add its Wisdom saving throw modifier to the saving throw.\n    On failure, it can still gesture, write, and otherwise communicate.\n    The affected creature cannot cast spells with verbal components until the spell ends.", "link": ""}, "cause serious wounds": {"name": "Cause Serious Wounds", "level": "4", "school": "Divine necromancy", "range": "Touch", "duration": "Instantaneous", "aoe": "Creature touched", "components": "V, S", "ct": "7 segments", "save": "None", "save_type": "", "description": "The touched target takes 2d8+1 hit points of magical damage, even if it can only be hit by magical weapons. Touching the target requires a successful to-hit roll; no saving throw is allowed.\nDetails:\nIf you miss the to-hit roll, no damage is inflicted and the spell is lost. This spell affects only naturally living creatures and does not affect golems, constructs, elementals, or undead.", "notes": "The touched target takes 2d8+1 hit points of magical damage, even if it can only be hit by magical weapons. Touching the target requires a successful to-hit roll; no saving throw is allowed.\nDetails:\nIf you miss the to-hit roll, no damage is inflicted and the spell is lost. This spell affects only naturally living creatures and does not affect golems, constructs, elementals, or undead.", "link": ""}, "cure serious wounds": {"name": "Cure Serious Wounds", "level": "4", "school": "Divine necromancy", "range": "Touch", "duration": "Instantaneous", "aoe": "Creature touched", "components": "V, S", "ct": "7 segments", "save": "None", "save_type": "", "description": "The target regains 2d8+1 hit points, up to its normal maximum. Any healing beyond the normal maximum is wasted.\nDetails:\nThis spell cannot cure disease, reattach limbs, raise the dead, or heal afflictions not measured in hit points; such effects require stronger magic. It generally affects only normally living creatures and has no effect on golems, constructs, elementals, or undead.\nReversible as Cause Serious Wounds:", "notes": "The target regains 2d8+1 hit points, up to its normal maximum. Any healing beyond the normal maximum is wasted.\nDetails:\nThis spell cannot cure disease, reattach limbs, raise the dead, or heal afflictions not measured in hit points; such effects require stronger magic. It generally affects only normally living creatures and has no effect on golems, constructs, elementals, or undead.\nReversible as Cause Serious Wounds:", "link": ""}, "detect lie": {"name": "Detect Lie", "level": "4", "school": "Divine divination", "range": "30 ft", "duration": "1 round per cleric level", "aoe": "One creature you designate", "components": "V, S, M", "ct": "7 segments", "save": "None", "save_type": "", "description": "Cast upon a specific creature. For the duration, when that creature speaks, you know whether it is saying something it does not believe to be true.\nDetails:\nYour awareness of lies is not detectable by others. The spell affects only speech, not telepathy or writing. You can only detect lies you can hear. Lies spoken in languages you do not know are still detected as lies, but you will not know what was actually said.\nReversible as Glibness:", "notes": "Cast upon a specific creature. For the duration, when that creature speaks, you know whether it is saying something it does not believe to be true.\nDetails:\nYour awareness of lies is not detectable by others. The spell affects only speech, not telepathy or writing. You can only detect lies you can hear. Lies spoken in languages you do not know are still detected as lies, but you will not know what was actually said.\nReversible as Glibness:", "link": ""}, "divination": {"name": "Divination", "level": "4", "school": "Divine divination", "range": "Caster", "duration": "1 round", "aoe": "Caster", "components": "V, S, M", "ct": "10 rounds", "save": "None", "save_type": "", "description": "Gives information about a place via divination (bones, yarrow stalks, tea leaves, entrails, etc.). You may misinterpret the reading.\nDetails:\n    The divination must be about a place. You do not need to be there; you need only its approximate location. It cannot be about an object unless it is so large it counts as a place (e.g., a building).\n    The GM secretly rolls 1d6:\n        1–4: You interpret correctly.\n        5–6: You interpret incorrectly.\n    If you sacrifice a magical item as part of the divination, it is destroyed and the GM’s d6 roll is modified by -1. Artifacts, relics, and equivalent items cannot be sacrificed or destroyed by this spell.\n    The GM provides your character’s interpretation of:\n        Whether the place is sacred to a god/demigod/power, and which;\n        Whether creatures inhabit it;\n        Whether those creatures are weak/equivalent/strong compared to you;\n        Whether treasure is present; and\n        Whether the treasure is poor/medium/rich.\n    If you misinterpret, the GM answers randomly with a mixture of correct and incorrect information.\n    Some legendary places are specially warded; divination always misinterprets those places.", "notes": "Gives information about a place via divination (bones, yarrow stalks, tea leaves, entrails, etc.). You may misinterpret the reading.\nDetails:\n    The divination must be about a place. You do not need to be there; you need only its approximate location. It cannot be about an object unless it is so large it counts as a place (e.g., a building).\n    The GM secretly rolls 1d6:\n        1–4: You interpret correctly.\n        5–6: You interpret incorrectly.\n    If you sacrifice a magical item as part of the divination, it is destroyed and the GM’s d6 roll is modified by -1. Artifacts, relics, and equivalent items cannot be sacrificed or destroyed by this spell.\n    The GM provides your character’s interpretation of:\n        Whether the place is sacred to a god/demigod/power, and which;\n        Whether creatures inhabit it;\n        Whether those creatures are weak/equivalent/strong compared to you;\n        Whether treasure is present; and\n        Whether the treasure is poor/medium/rich.\n    If you misinterpret, the GM answers randomly with a mixture of correct and incorrect information.\n    Some legendary places are specially warded; divination always misinterprets those places.", "link": ""}, "exorcise": {"name": "Exorcise", "level": "4", "school": "Divine abjuration", "range": "10 ft", "duration": "Instantaneous (or continuing; see below)", "aoe": "One creature, object, or place", "components": "V, S, M", "ct": "10 rounds, continuing", "save": "Depends on use (see below)", "save_type": "", "description": "A multi-purpose ritual to cast out a supernatural creature or influence (fiend, ghost, etc.) possessing a creature/object. It can also remove a curse or end a charm/enchantment. The casting and effect are loud.\nDetails:\nUsing the spell to remove curses / end charm or enchantment:\n    Automatically succeeds when you finish the first turn of casting.\n    Unwilling targets do not receive a saving throw for this use.\nUsing the spell to cast out supernatural creatures and influences:\n    On a good-aligned outer plane: automatically succeeds after the first turn.\n    On an evil-aligned outer plane: automatically fails.\n    Otherwise, each turn you continue casting, the creature/influence rolls a special saving throw on d20; failure means it is exorcised.\nSaving throws versus exorcism (base target numbers):\nCreature/Influence Strength\tBase Saving Throw\nWeak influence, dretch, spiked devil\t10\nModerate influence, class A demon, shub demon, bearded devil, erinyes, scaly devil\t8\nClass B demon, uduk demon, ekivu demon, ghost, succubus, barbed devil\t7\nClass C demon, babau demon, bone devil\t6\nStrong influence, class D demon, horned devil\t5\nClass E demon, ice devil, night hag\t4\nClass F demon, pit fiend, shaitan devil\t3\nModifiers:\n    Apply -1 to the creature’s saving throw for each cleric level you have above 8.\n    If you hold a relevant artifact/relic, the GM may assign an additional -1 to -4 modifier (based on strength/aptitude/inclination).\n    Magic resistance does not apply.\n    On a natural 20 on its saving throw, you suffer an ill effect (e.g., curse or loss of 1 point from a random ability score).\n    Cannot exorcise artifacts, relics, deities, or equivalent powers.\nEffect of exorcism:\nThe cast-out creature returns to its own body (or nearest body if it has several). If bodiless, it appears on the Prime Material Plane adjacent to the formerly possessed target (GM chooses or randomises if multiple possible).", "notes": "A multi-purpose ritual to cast out a supernatural creature or influence (fiend, ghost, etc.) possessing a creature/object. It can also remove a curse or end a charm/enchantment. The casting and effect are loud.\nDetails:\nUsing the spell to remove curses / end charm or enchantment:\n    Automatically succeeds when you finish the first turn of casting.\n    Unwilling targets do not receive a saving throw for this use.\nUsing the spell to cast out supernatural creatures and influences:\n    On a good-aligned outer plane: automatically succeeds after the first turn.\n    On an evil-aligned outer plane: automatically fails.\n    Otherwise, each turn you continue casting, the creature/influence rolls a special saving throw on d20; failure means it is exorcised.\nSaving throws versus exorcism (base target numbers):\nCreature/Influence Strength\tBase Saving Throw\nWeak influence, dretch, spiked devil\t10\nModerate influence, class A demon, shub demon, bearded devil, erinyes, scaly devil\t8\nClass B demon, uduk demon, ekivu demon, ghost, succubus, barbed devil\t7\nClass C demon, babau demon, bone devil\t6\nStrong influence, class D demon, horned devil\t5\nClass E demon, ice devil, night hag\t4\nClass F demon, pit fiend, shaitan devil\t3\nModifiers:\n    Apply -1 to the creature’s saving throw for each cleric level you have above 8.\n    If you hold a relevant artifact/relic, the GM may assign an additional -1 to -4 modifier (based on strength/aptitude/inclination).\n    Magic resistance does not apply.\n    On a natural 20 on its saving throw, you suffer an ill effect (e.g., curse or loss of 1 point from a random ability score).\n    Cannot exorcise artifacts, relics, deities, or equivalent powers.\nEffect of exorcism:\nThe cast-out creature returns to its own body (or nearest body if it has several). If bodiless, it appears on the Prime Material Plane adjacent to the formerly possessed target (GM chooses or randomises if multiple possible).", "link": ""}, "glibness": {"name": "Glibness", "level": "4", "school": "Divine transmutation", "range": "30 ft", "duration": "1 round per cleric level", "aoe": "One creature", "components": "V, S, M", "ct": "7 segments", "save": "None", "save_type": "", "description": "Counters detect lie on the target; if detect lie is not in effect, the target’s lies become more convincing.\nDetails:\n    A creature can only be affected by one instance of this spell at a time.\n    As with most targeted spells, you can cast it on yourself or another creature.\n    Lies are only believed if the listener can hear and understand them.\n    The GM determines plausibility; each listener then rolls a special saving throw on a d20 (optionally adding their Wisdom save modifier).\nSaving throw targets for Glibness:\nPlausibility\tSaving Throw Target\nLikely\t20\nPlausible\t18\nPossible\t15\nSurprising\t11\nUnlikely\t7\nObviously false\t2\nIf the listener passes, they do not believe the lie.", "notes": "Counters detect lie on the target; if detect lie is not in effect, the target’s lies become more convincing.\nDetails:\n    A creature can only be affected by one instance of this spell at a time.\n    As with most targeted spells, you can cast it on yourself or another creature.\n    Lies are only believed if the listener can hear and understand them.\n    The GM determines plausibility; each listener then rolls a special saving throw on a d20 (optionally adding their Wisdom save modifier).\nSaving throw targets for Glibness:\nPlausibility\tSaving Throw Target\nLikely\t20\nPlausible\t18\nPossible\t15\nSurprising\t11\nUnlikely\t7\nObviously false\t2\nIf the listener passes, they do not believe the lie.", "link": ""}, "lower water": {"name": "Lower Water", "level": "4", "school": "Divine transmutation", "range": "120 ft", "duration": "1 turn per cleric level", "aoe": "Up to 10 ft square of surface area per cleric level", "components": "V, S, M", "ct": "10 rounds", "save": "None", "save_type": "", "description": "Water in the affected area sinks by 5 ft. If you can affect the same area multiple times, you may lower it an additional 5 ft per iteration.\nExample: A 30 ft × 30 ft pool: you can affect a 30 ft square once per 3 cleric levels. At level 7–8 you can lower by 10 ft; 9–11 by 15 ft; 12–14 by 20 ft; etc.\nDisplaced water is held in a magical interdimensional space for the spell’s duration and returns when the spell ends (slightly chilled).\nDetails:\nTarget liquid must be non-magical and roughly water-like viscosity (blood might work; lava would not). If the target is a water creature (water weird/elemental), it is considered held unless the monster description says otherwise.\nReversible as Raise Water:", "notes": "Water in the affected area sinks by 5 ft. If you can affect the same area multiple times, you may lower it an additional 5 ft per iteration.\nExample: A 30 ft × 30 ft pool: you can affect a 30 ft square once per 3 cleric levels. At level 7–8 you can lower by 10 ft; 9–11 by 15 ft; 12–14 by 20 ft; etc.\nDisplaced water is held in a magical interdimensional space for the spell’s duration and returns when the spell ends (slightly chilled).\nDetails:\nTarget liquid must be non-magical and roughly water-like viscosity (blood might work; lava would not). If the target is a water creature (water weird/elemental), it is considered held unless the monster description says otherwise.\nReversible as Raise Water:", "link": ""}, "neutralise poison": {"name": "Neutralise Poison", "level": "4", "school": "Divine transmutation", "range": "Touch", "duration": "Instantaneous", "aoe": "1 ft cube per 2 cleric levels, or one creature", "components": "V, S", "ct": "7 segments", "save": "Depends on use (see below)", "save_type": "", "description": "Purges venom/toxin/contaminant, rendering it harmless. Can potentially revive someone who has recently “died” from poison.\nDetails:\n    Does not affect disease-based contamination.\n    Gods/demigods/artifacts/relics/equivalent are not affected (GM may allow some derivative effects to be affected).\n    If targeting a toxic place, all toxins/contaminants are purged from the area.\nUsing the spell to de-venom an opponent:\n    If the target is a creature, it may choose a saving throw vs spells and other magical effects.\n        Success: not affected.\n        Failure: if it has a venomous attack, the venom component is nullified until dawn the next day.\nUsing the spell to revive someone “dead by poison”:\n    If the target is poisoned, all toxins are purged, but poison damage already taken remains.\n    Also works on creatures that have recently died of poison: death from poison damage or failed save vs poison within a number of turns equal to your cleric level.\nReversible as Poison:", "notes": "Purges venom/toxin/contaminant, rendering it harmless. Can potentially revive someone who has recently “died” from poison.\nDetails:\n    Does not affect disease-based contamination.\n    Gods/demigods/artifacts/relics/equivalent are not affected (GM may allow some derivative effects to be affected).\n    If targeting a toxic place, all toxins/contaminants are purged from the area.\nUsing the spell to de-venom an opponent:\n    If the target is a creature, it may choose a saving throw vs spells and other magical effects.\n        Success: not affected.\n        Failure: if it has a venomous attack, the venom component is nullified until dawn the next day.\nUsing the spell to revive someone “dead by poison”:\n    If the target is poisoned, all toxins are purged, but poison damage already taken remains.\n    Also works on creatures that have recently died of poison: death from poison damage or failed save vs poison within a number of turns equal to your cleric level.\nReversible as Poison:", "link": ""}, "poison": {"name": "Poison", "level": "4", "school": "Divine transmutation", "range": "Touch", "duration": "Instantaneous", "aoe": "1 ft cube per 2 cleric levels, including no more than one creature", "components": "V, S", "ct": "7 segments", "save": "Depends on use (see below)", "save_type": "", "description": "Your touch becomes deadly poison, or you can make an edible/potable substance poisonous. In either case, you must touch the target.\nDetails:\n    If targeting a creature, it may attempt a saving throw vs poison; success negates.\n    Creatures immune to poison are unaffected.\n    Gods/demigods/artifacts/relics/equivalent are unaffected.\n    If a creature fails its save: it dies.\n    If an edible/potable is poisoned: the first creature to consume must save vs poison or die (unless immune). After that save is resolved, remaining poison is nullified.", "notes": "Your touch becomes deadly poison, or you can make an edible/potable substance poisonous. In either case, you must touch the target.\nDetails:\n    If targeting a creature, it may attempt a saving throw vs poison; success negates.\n    Creatures immune to poison are unaffected.\n    Gods/demigods/artifacts/relics/equivalent are unaffected.\n    If a creature fails its save: it dies.\n    If an edible/potable is poisoned: the first creature to consume must save vs poison or die (unless immune). After that save is resolved, remaining poison is nullified.", "link": ""}, "protection from evil 10 ft radius": {"name": "Protection from Evil 10 Ft Radius", "level": "4", "school": "Divine abjuration", "range": "Touch", "duration": "10 rounds per cleric level", "aoe": "10 ft radius around the creature touched", "components": "V, S, M", "ct": "7 segments", "save": "None", "save_type": "", "description": "Creates a 10 ft radius invisible barrier against evil and summoned creatures around the protected creature.\nDetails:\n    Cast on yourself or another willing creature; not on hostile creatures, objects, or places.\n    A creature can only be affected by one instance at a time. If already warded by the 1st-level protection from evil, this spell has no effect on it.\n    Effects within the warded area:\n        Evil creatures: -2 to attack rolls into the warded area; anyone inside gains +2 on saving throws caused by evil creatures or their effects.\n        Evil effects (rare): effects explicitly described as evil/fiendish/demonic/devilish allow +2 to saving throws.\n        Summoned/conjured creatures: cannot attack into the warded area by touch (claws, teeth, etc.), regardless of alignment. They only suffer the -2 penalty in (1) if they are evil. (A non-evil summoned creature could still attack with a long weapon if it can reach.)\n    Ghouls: additionally “kept at bay” (cannot reduce distance to the warded area), but if the warded area moves toward them, they need not retreat. Some GMs extend “kept at bay” beyond ghouls.\nReversible as Protection from Good 10 ft Radius:", "notes": "Creates a 10 ft radius invisible barrier against evil and summoned creatures around the protected creature.\nDetails:\n    Cast on yourself or another willing creature; not on hostile creatures, objects, or places.\n    A creature can only be affected by one instance at a time. If already warded by the 1st-level protection from evil, this spell has no effect on it.\n    Effects within the warded area:\n        Evil creatures: -2 to attack rolls into the warded area; anyone inside gains +2 on saving throws caused by evil creatures or their effects.\n        Evil effects (rare): effects explicitly described as evil/fiendish/demonic/devilish allow +2 to saving throws.\n        Summoned/conjured creatures: cannot attack into the warded area by touch (claws, teeth, etc.), regardless of alignment. They only suffer the -2 penalty in (1) if they are evil. (A non-evil summoned creature could still attack with a long weapon if it can reach.)\n    Ghouls: additionally “kept at bay” (cannot reduce distance to the warded area), but if the warded area moves toward them, they need not retreat. Some GMs extend “kept at bay” beyond ghouls.\nReversible as Protection from Good 10 ft Radius:", "link": ""}, "protection from good 10 ft radius": {"name": "Protection from Good 10 Ft Radius", "level": "4", "school": "Divine abjuration", "range": "Touch", "duration": "10 rounds per cleric level", "aoe": "10 ft radius around the creature touched", "components": "V, S, M", "ct": "7 segments", "save": "None", "save_type": "", "description": "Creates a 10 ft radius barrier against good-aligned and summoned creatures around the protected creature.\nDetails:\n    Same targeting limits and stacking limits as the evil version (and does not affect a creature already warded by 1st-level protection from good).\n    Effects:\n        Good creatures: -2 to attack rolls into the warded area; anyone inside gains +2 on saving throws caused by good creatures or their effects.\n        Holy effects (rare): effects explicitly described as “holy” allow +2 to saving throws.\n        Summoned/conjured creatures: cannot attack into the warded area by touch, regardless of alignment; only take the -2 penalty if actually good-aligned. (A non-good summoned creature could still attack with a long weapon if it can reach.)", "notes": "Creates a 10 ft radius barrier against good-aligned and summoned creatures around the protected creature.\nDetails:\n    Same targeting limits and stacking limits as the evil version (and does not affect a creature already warded by 1st-level protection from good).\n    Effects:\n        Good creatures: -2 to attack rolls into the warded area; anyone inside gains +2 on saving throws caused by good creatures or their effects.\n        Holy effects (rare): effects explicitly described as “holy” allow +2 to saving throws.\n        Summoned/conjured creatures: cannot attack into the warded area by touch, regardless of alignment; only take the -2 penalty if actually good-aligned. (A non-good summoned creature could still attack with a long weapon if it can reach.)", "link": ""}, "raise water": {"name": "Raise Water", "level": "4", "school": "Divine transmutation", "range": "120 ft", "duration": "1 turn per cleric level", "aoe": "Up to 10 ft square of surface area per cleric level", "components": "V, S, M", "ct": "10 rounds", "save": "None", "save_type": "", "description": "Water in the affected area rises by 5 ft. If you can affect the same area multiple times, you may raise it an additional 5 ft per iteration.\nDetails:\nAdditional water comes from the Elemental Plane of Water for the duration and returns when the spell ends (about room temperature). Target liquid must be non-magical and roughly water-like viscosity. If the target is a water creature (water weird/elemental), it is affected as if by an enlarge spell.", "notes": "Water in the affected area rises by 5 ft. If you can affect the same area multiple times, you may raise it an additional 5 ft per iteration.\nDetails:\nAdditional water comes from the Elemental Plane of Water for the duration and returns when the spell ends (about room temperature). Target liquid must be non-magical and roughly water-like viscosity. If the target is a water creature (water weird/elemental), it is affected as if by an enlarge spell.", "link": ""}, "snakes to sticks": {"name": "Snakes to Sticks", "level": "4", "school": "Divine transmutation", "range": "30 ft", "duration": "2 rounds per cleric level", "aoe": "10 ft cube", "components": "V, S, M", "ct": "7 segments", "save": "Yes (negates effect)", "save_type": "", "description": "Transforms ophidian creatures into sticks temporarily. Affects snakes, serpents, couatls, nagas, and similar; maximum of one creature per cleric level.\nDetails:\n    Targets may save vs spells and other magical effects; success negates.\n    If unclear, affected creatures include those listed above and other reptilian creatures that lacked limbs when hatched. Dragons, demons, devils, and wyverns are not “snakes” for this spell.\n    Some ophidian creatures are too large to fit in the area and cannot be affected.\n    While wood, snakes can be broken/burned/destroyed; if destroyed, they are dead when the spell ends.", "notes": "Transforms ophidian creatures into sticks temporarily. Affects snakes, serpents, couatls, nagas, and similar; maximum of one creature per cleric level.\nDetails:\n    Targets may save vs spells and other magical effects; success negates.\n    If unclear, affected creatures include those listed above and other reptilian creatures that lacked limbs when hatched. Dragons, demons, devils, and wyverns are not “snakes” for this spell.\n    Some ophidian creatures are too large to fit in the area and cannot be affected.\n    While wood, snakes can be broken/burned/destroyed; if destroyed, they are dead when the spell ends.", "link": ""}, "speak with plants": {"name": "Speak with Plants", "level": "4", "school": "Divine transmutation", "range": "30 ft", "duration": "1 round per cleric level", "aoe": "One plant within range", "components": "V, S", "ct": "10 rounds", "save": "None", "save_type": "", "description": "Lets you communicate with a nearby plant and understand its “speech.”\nDetails:\n    Only you hear the magical translation.\n    You speak in Common; the plant understands. It replies in its natural mode; the spell translates into your mind.\n    Some plants may be mobile/dangerous; you can bargain/persuade/deceive as appropriate.\n    GM decides what counts as a “plant.”\n    The plant usually won’t start combat until the spell ends, but if you/your allies attacked it in the last turn, it is not required to stop fighting.\n    Does not compel truth.", "notes": "Lets you communicate with a nearby plant and understand its “speech.”\nDetails:\n    Only you hear the magical translation.\n    You speak in Common; the plant understands. It replies in its natural mode; the spell translates into your mind.\n    Some plants may be mobile/dangerous; you can bargain/persuade/deceive as appropriate.\n    GM decides what counts as a “plant.”\n    The plant usually won’t start combat until the spell ends, but if you/your allies attacked it in the last turn, it is not required to stop fighting.\n    Does not compel truth.", "link": ""}, "sticks to snakes": {"name": "Sticks to Snakes", "level": "4", "school": "Divine transmutation", "range": "30 ft", "duration": "2 rounds per cleric level", "aoe": "10 ft cube; max 1 stick per cleric level", "components": "V, S, M", "ct": "7 segments", "save": "None", "save_type": "", "description": "Transforms dead wood into serpents. The serpents do not understand speech, but obey mental commands to attack a target.\nFor each snake created, roll 1d20: if the result is ≤ your cleric level, the snake is venomous; otherwise it is a constrictor.\nDetails:\n    Affects roughly cylindrical dead-wood objects, up to a maximum number equal to your cleric level. Targets cannot be magical.\n    If you aren’t in a forest, bring your own sticks.\nVenomous Snake: AC 6, MV 90 ft, HD 2, #AT 1, Dmg 1 piercing, SA poison (save vs poison or die; apply CON modifier to save), Size S, AL N.\nConstrictor Snake: AC 6, MV 90 ft, HD 2, #AT 1, Dmg 1 blunt, SA constrict (on hit: constricts until it releases or is killed; one target at a time; may deal 1d4 blunt damage on its initiative instead of attacking), Size S, AL N.\nNo XP is awarded for killing/defeating snakes created by this spell.\nReversible as Snakes to Sticks:", "notes": "Transforms dead wood into serpents. The serpents do not understand speech, but obey mental commands to attack a target.\nFor each snake created, roll 1d20: if the result is ≤ your cleric level, the snake is venomous; otherwise it is a constrictor.\nDetails:\n    Affects roughly cylindrical dead-wood objects, up to a maximum number equal to your cleric level. Targets cannot be magical.\n    If you aren’t in a forest, bring your own sticks.\nVenomous Snake: AC 6, MV 90 ft, HD 2, #AT 1, Dmg 1 piercing, SA poison (save vs poison or die; apply CON modifier to save), Size S, AL N.\nConstrictor Snake: AC 6, MV 90 ft, HD 2, #AT 1, Dmg 1 blunt, SA constrict (on hit: constricts until it releases or is killed; one target at a time; may deal 1d4 blunt damage on its initiative instead of attacking), Size S, AL N.\nNo XP is awarded for killing/defeating snakes created by this spell.\nReversible as Snakes to Sticks:", "link": ""}, "tongues": {"name": "Tongues", "level": "4", "school": "Divine divination", "range": "Caster", "duration": "1 turn", "aoe": "30 ft radius around you", "components": "V, S, M", "ct": "7 segments", "save": "None", "save_type": "", "description": "Magically translates spoken language for you and translates your words for other creatures within the area.\nDetails:\n    Only you hear the translation of others’ speech, and only if spoken within the area.\n    Everyone in the area hears the translation of your words.\n    Spoken words only; writing and non-verbal communication are unaffected.\n    Creatures only understand you if they naturally speak at least one language.\nReversible as Blither:", "notes": "Magically translates spoken language for you and translates your words for other creatures within the area.\nDetails:\n    Only you hear the translation of others’ speech, and only if spoken within the area.\n    Everyone in the area hears the translation of your words.\n    Spoken words only; writing and non-verbal communication are unaffected.\n    Creatures only understand you if they naturally speak at least one language.\nReversible as Blither:", "link": ""}, "atonement": {"name": "Atonement", "level": "5", "school": "Divine abjuration", "range": "Touch", "duration": "Instantaneous", "aoe": "One creature", "components": "V, S, M", "ct": "10 rounds", "save": "None", "save_type": "", "description": "You request forgiveness for the target’s past sins and transgressions. Any punishments imposed by gods or spirits are removed (see details). The spell can only be cast on a willing creature.\nDetails:\nThe spell ends without effect if:\n    Your alignment is chaotic and the target’s is lawful;\n    Your alignment is lawful and the target’s is chaotic;\n    Your alignment is good and the target’s is evil; or\n    Your alignment is evil and the target’s is good.\nIf the target’s transgressions were involuntary, unwilling, or unwitting, and the target is truly sorry, punishments are lifted unconditionally.\nIf the transgressions were involuntary, unwilling, or unwitting, and the target is not truly sorry, the gods/spirits assign a penance or quest; punishments are lifted when it is completed.\nIf the transgressions occurred while the target’s mind/brain was disturbed (charm, domination, mind control, possession), and the disturbance is ongoing, punishments are lifted unconditionally regardless of remorse, and the disturbance ends.\nIf the transgressions were voluntary but the target honestly believed they were for the greater good, the GM determines whether the repentance is accepted. If accepted, a penance/quest is assigned; punishments are lifted when it is completed.", "notes": "You request forgiveness for the target’s past sins and transgressions. Any punishments imposed by gods or spirits are removed (see details). The spell can only be cast on a willing creature.\nDetails:\nThe spell ends without effect if:\n    Your alignment is chaotic and the target’s is lawful;\n    Your alignment is lawful and the target’s is chaotic;\n    Your alignment is good and the target’s is evil; or\n    Your alignment is evil and the target’s is good.\nIf the target’s transgressions were involuntary, unwilling, or unwitting, and the target is truly sorry, punishments are lifted unconditionally.\nIf the transgressions were involuntary, unwilling, or unwitting, and the target is not truly sorry, the gods/spirits assign a penance or quest; punishments are lifted when it is completed.\nIf the transgressions occurred while the target’s mind/brain was disturbed (charm, domination, mind control, possession), and the disturbance is ongoing, punishments are lifted unconditionally regardless of remorse, and the disturbance ends.\nIf the transgressions were voluntary but the target honestly believed they were for the greater good, the GM determines whether the repentance is accepted. If accepted, a penance/quest is assigned; punishments are lifted when it is completed.", "link": ""}, "cause critical wounds": {"name": "Cause Critical Wounds", "level": "5", "school": "Divine necromancy", "range": "Touch", "duration": "Instantaneous", "aoe": "Creature touched", "components": "V, S", "ct": "8 segments", "save": "None", "save_type": "", "description": "The touched target takes 3d8+3 magical damage, even if it can only be hit by magical weapons. Requires a successful to-hit roll; no saving throw allowed.\nDetails:\nIf you miss the to-hit roll, no damage is inflicted and the spell is lost. Affects normally living creatures only; no effect on golems, constructs, elementals, or undead.", "notes": "The touched target takes 3d8+3 magical damage, even if it can only be hit by magical weapons. Requires a successful to-hit roll; no saving throw allowed.\nDetails:\nIf you miss the to-hit roll, no damage is inflicted and the spell is lost. Affects normally living creatures only; no effect on golems, constructs, elementals, or undead.", "link": ""}, "commune": {"name": "Commune", "level": "5", "school": "Divine divination", "range": "Self", "duration": "3 rounds", "aoe": "You", "components": "V, S, M", "ct": "10 rounds", "save": "None", "save_type": "", "description": "You pray for enlightenment; an invisible divine power answers your questions.\nDetails:\nGods/spirits that are pestered too often may choose not to respond.\nThe divine emissary knows what the gods/spirits you petition know. It is not omniscient, but its knowledge of the Prime Material Plane is likely excellent. It never lies.\nYou may ask one question per cleric level. Each must be asked promptly and respectfully or the emissary departs, ending the spell without further effect. Each answer is:\n“O [adjective] mortal, the answer to your question is…” followed by “yes”, “no”, “I don’t know”, or “it’s complicated”. The emissary may add an adjective before “mortal” (commonly “puny” or “insignificant”, but possibly “annoying”, “stupid”, etc. if patience wears thin).\nOnly you can hear the responses.", "notes": "You pray for enlightenment; an invisible divine power answers your questions.\nDetails:\nGods/spirits that are pestered too often may choose not to respond.\nThe divine emissary knows what the gods/spirits you petition know. It is not omniscient, but its knowledge of the Prime Material Plane is likely excellent. It never lies.\nYou may ask one question per cleric level. Each must be asked promptly and respectfully or the emissary departs, ending the spell without further effect. Each answer is:\n“O [adjective] mortal, the answer to your question is…” followed by “yes”, “no”, “I don’t know”, or “it’s complicated”. The emissary may add an adjective before “mortal” (commonly “puny” or “insignificant”, but possibly “annoying”, “stupid”, etc. if patience wears thin).\nOnly you can hear the responses.", "link": ""}, "cure critical wounds": {"name": "Cure Critical Wounds", "level": "5", "school": "Divine necromancy", "range": "Touch", "duration": "Instantaneous", "aoe": "Creature touched", "components": "V, S", "ct": "8 segments", "save": "None", "save_type": "", "description": "The target regains 3d8+3 hp, up to its normal maximum. Healing beyond maximum is wasted.\nDetails:\nDoes not cure disease, reattach limbs, raise the dead, or heal afflictions not measured in hit points. Generally affects only normally living creatures; no effect on golems, constructs, elementals, or undead.\nReversible as Cause Critical Wounds:", "notes": "The target regains 3d8+3 hp, up to its normal maximum. Healing beyond maximum is wasted.\nDetails:\nDoes not cure disease, reattach limbs, raise the dead, or heal afflictions not measured in hit points. Generally affects only normally living creatures; no effect on golems, constructs, elementals, or undead.\nReversible as Cause Critical Wounds:", "link": ""}, "dispel evil": {"name": "Dispel Evil", "level": "5", "school": "Divine abjuration", "range": "Touch", "duration": "1 round per cleric level", "aoe": "Creature touched", "components": "V, S, M", "ct": "8 segments", "save": "Yes (lessened effect)", "save_type": "", "description": "Banishes an evil-aligned extraplanar creature. It disappears with an audible “pop”.\nDetails:\nTarget applies its Wisdom save modifier (if any) to the saving throw.\n    Fail save: banished to its home plane.\n    Pass save: not banished, but for the spell’s duration, whenever it attacks you with melee/missile/touch, you may choose to apply -7 to its attack roll.\nWorks only on evil creatures from other planes (demons, devils, efreets, etc.). The banished creature takes its carried/worn items, but no other creatures go with it even if it is carrying them.\nReversible as Dispel Good:", "notes": "Banishes an evil-aligned extraplanar creature. It disappears with an audible “pop”.\nDetails:\nTarget applies its Wisdom save modifier (if any) to the saving throw.\n    Fail save: banished to its home plane.\n    Pass save: not banished, but for the spell’s duration, whenever it attacks you with melee/missile/touch, you may choose to apply -7 to its attack roll.\nWorks only on evil creatures from other planes (demons, devils, efreets, etc.). The banished creature takes its carried/worn items, but no other creatures go with it even if it is carrying them.\nReversible as Dispel Good:", "link": ""}, "dispel good": {"name": "Dispel Good", "level": "5", "school": "Divine abjuration", "range": "Touch", "duration": "1 round per cleric level", "aoe": "Creature touched", "components": "V, S, M", "ct": "8 segments", "save": "Yes (lessened effect)", "save_type": "", "description": "Banishes a good-aligned extraplanar creature; it disappears with an audible “pop”.\nDetails:\nTarget applies its Wisdom save modifier (if any) to the saving throw.\n    Fail save: banished to its home plane.\n    Pass save: not banished, but for the spell’s duration, whenever it attacks you with melee/missile/touch, you may choose to apply -7 to its attack roll.\nWorks only on good extraplanar creatures (celestials, genies, etc.). The banished creature takes carried/worn items only.", "notes": "Banishes a good-aligned extraplanar creature; it disappears with an audible “pop”.\nDetails:\nTarget applies its Wisdom save modifier (if any) to the saving throw.\n    Fail save: banished to its home plane.\n    Pass save: not banished, but for the spell’s duration, whenever it attacks you with melee/missile/touch, you may choose to apply -7 to its attack roll.\nWorks only on good extraplanar creatures (celestials, genies, etc.). The banished creature takes carried/worn items only.", "link": ""}, "false seeing": {"name": "False Seeing", "level": "5", "school": "Divine divination", "range": "Touch", "duration": "1 round per cleric level", "aoe": "120 ft radius around the touched creature", "components": "V, S, M", "ct": "8 segments", "save": "Yes (negates effect)", "save_type": "", "description": "Affects one creature: it suffers wild hallucinations, is blinded for the duration, and must make a morale check each round or flee screaming in a random direction.\nDetails:\nTarget adds its Wisdom save modifier to the saving throw.", "notes": "Affects one creature: it suffers wild hallucinations, is blinded for the duration, and must make a morale check each round or flee screaming in a random direction.\nDetails:\nTarget adds its Wisdom save modifier to the saving throw.", "link": ""}, "flame strike": {"name": "Flame Strike", "level": "5", "school": "Divine evocation", "range": "60 ft", "duration": "Instantaneous", "aoe": "Column, 5 ft radius; 30 ft high", "components": "V, S, M", "ct": "8 segments", "save": "Yes (half damage)", "save_type": "", "description": "Cast at a visible target point on the ground. A pillar of flame strikes; extremely loud (heard within 300 ft).\nDetails:\nCreatures in the area take 6d8 fire damage. If any fiends or celestials are in the area, they instead take 6d8 magical damage (not fire).\nCreatures may save vs spells/magical effects:\n    Pass: half damage; worn/carried items are undamaged.\n    Fail/decline: full damage; roll item saves vs fire for worn/carried objects.\nGM rolls saves vs fire for unattended objects in the area. In 5 ft squares, can hit up to 4 squares (target an intersection). Afterward, the area is charred/sooty with a lingering scent appropriate to the invoked power (incense, brimstone, etc.).", "notes": "Cast at a visible target point on the ground. A pillar of flame strikes; extremely loud (heard within 300 ft).\nDetails:\nCreatures in the area take 6d8 fire damage. If any fiends or celestials are in the area, they instead take 6d8 magical damage (not fire).\nCreatures may save vs spells/magical effects:\n    Pass: half damage; worn/carried items are undamaged.\n    Fail/decline: full damage; roll item saves vs fire for worn/carried objects.\nGM rolls saves vs fire for unattended objects in the area. In 5 ft squares, can hit up to 4 squares (target an intersection). Afterward, the area is charred/sooty with a lingering scent appropriate to the invoked power (incense, brimstone, etc.).", "link": ""}, "insect plague": {"name": "Insect Plague", "level": "5", "school": "Divine conjuration", "range": "360 ft", "duration": "10 rounds per cleric level", "aoe": "Column, 180 ft radius; 60 ft high", "components": "V, S, M", "ct": "10 rounds", "save": "None", "save_type": "", "description": "Conjures a swarm of biting/stinging insects from a visible target point on the ground.\nDetails:\nIf you are level 18 or lower: mundane insects (wasps, clegs, midges, mosquitoes, biting locusts). Each round, at the start of the round, each creature in the area:\n    Takes 1 point piercing damage; and\n    Level 2 / 2 HD or less: must flee until at least 240 ft from the plague’s edge.\n    Level 4 / 4 HD or less: must check morale; on failure, flee until at least 120 ft from the edge.\nIf you are level 19 or higher: may conjure extraplanar insects. Each round, at the start of the round, each creature in the area:\n    Takes 2 points piercing damage; and\n    Level 4 / 4 HD or less: must flee until at least 240 ft from the edge.\n    Level 7 / 7 HD or less: must check morale; on failure, flee until at least 120 ft from the edge.\nOther details:\n    Fire/smoke holds back insects while it lasts (e.g., wall of fire works; fireball/flame strike only clears briefly).\n    Insects can pass through tiny spaces but not impenetrable barriers (can pass through blade barrier/wall of thorns; not wall of force).\n    Insects will not enter water; fully submerged creatures at start of round take no damage.\n    Creatures immune to mundane weapons are unaffected, regardless of HD.\n    Visibility inside is 30 ft.", "notes": "Conjures a swarm of biting/stinging insects from a visible target point on the ground.\nDetails:\nIf you are level 18 or lower: mundane insects (wasps, clegs, midges, mosquitoes, biting locusts). Each round, at the start of the round, each creature in the area:\n    Takes 1 point piercing damage; and\n    Level 2 / 2 HD or less: must flee until at least 240 ft from the plague’s edge.\n    Level 4 / 4 HD or less: must check morale; on failure, flee until at least 120 ft from the edge.\nIf you are level 19 or higher: may conjure extraplanar insects. Each round, at the start of the round, each creature in the area:\n    Takes 2 points piercing damage; and\n    Level 4 / 4 HD or less: must flee until at least 240 ft from the edge.\n    Level 7 / 7 HD or less: must check morale; on failure, flee until at least 120 ft from the edge.\nOther details:\n    Fire/smoke holds back insects while it lasts (e.g., wall of fire works; fireball/flame strike only clears briefly).\n    Insects can pass through tiny spaces but not impenetrable barriers (can pass through blade barrier/wall of thorns; not wall of force).\n    Insects will not enter water; fully submerged creatures at start of round take no damage.\n    Creatures immune to mundane weapons are unaffected, regardless of HD.\n    Visibility inside is 30 ft.", "link": ""}, "plane shift": {"name": "Plane Shift", "level": "5", "school": "Divine conjuration", "range": "Touch", "duration": "Instantaneous", "aoe": "Creatures touched", "components": "V, S, M", "ct": "8 segments", "save": "Depends on use (see below)", "save_type": "", "description": "Transports either:\n    One unwilling creature, or\n    Up to 7 willing creatures holding hands in a circle, plus optionally the caster,\n    to an Outer Plane.\nIf the creature is native to an Outer Plane, it returns to its origin plane; otherwise the caster chooses which Outer Plane it is sent to.\nDetails:\nIf you touch an unwilling creature, it may attempt a saving throw vs spells/magical effects, adding its Wisdom save modifier. On success, the spell does not affect it.", "notes": "Transports either:\n    One unwilling creature, or\n    Up to 7 willing creatures holding hands in a circle, plus optionally the caster,\n    to an Outer Plane.\nIf the creature is native to an Outer Plane, it returns to its origin plane; otherwise the caster chooses which Outer Plane it is sent to.\nDetails:\nIf you touch an unwilling creature, it may attempt a saving throw vs spells/magical effects, adding its Wisdom save modifier. On success, the spell does not affect it.", "link": ""}, "quest": {"name": "Quest", "level": "5", "school": "Divine enchantment", "range": "60 ft", "duration": "Until completed", "aoe": "Creature touched", "components": "V, S, M", "ct": "8 segments", "save": "Yes (negates effect)", "save_type": "", "description": "Sets a quest a target creature is compelled to perform. Target must be human, demi-human, or humanoid.\nDetails:\nTarget may save vs spells/other effects, adding Wisdom save modifier. On success, spell ends without effect.\nQuest limitations:\n    Cannot be one that would change the target’s alignment if completed.\n    Must be within the target’s power.\n    Must be possible to complete within a year and a day.\nEnding conditions:\n    You can end it at any time.\n    Any cleric higher level than you can end it by touching the target and willing it to end.\n    Ends when the target returns with proof of completion (or, if it doesn’t know where you are, to the casting location), or when the target dies, or when completion becomes impossible (target of assassination dies; object to retrieve is destroyed; etc.).\nPenalty for procrastination:\nFor each 24 hours the target avoids the quest, it takes a cumulative -1 to all saving throws (periods need not be continuous). Normal daily maintenance is allowed as long as it is acting in good faith toward the quest.", "notes": "Sets a quest a target creature is compelled to perform. Target must be human, demi-human, or humanoid.\nDetails:\nTarget may save vs spells/other effects, adding Wisdom save modifier. On success, spell ends without effect.\nQuest limitations:\n    Cannot be one that would change the target’s alignment if completed.\n    Must be within the target’s power.\n    Must be possible to complete within a year and a day.\nEnding conditions:\n    You can end it at any time.\n    Any cleric higher level than you can end it by touching the target and willing it to end.\n    Ends when the target returns with proof of completion (or, if it doesn’t know where you are, to the casting location), or when the target dies, or when completion becomes impossible (target of assassination dies; object to retrieve is destroyed; etc.).\nPenalty for procrastination:\nFor each 24 hours the target avoids the quest, it takes a cumulative -1 to all saving throws (periods need not be continuous). Normal daily maintenance is allowed as long as it is acting in good faith toward the quest.", "link": ""}, "raise dead": {"name": "Raise Dead", "level": "5", "school": "Divine necromancy", "range": "30 ft", "duration": "Instantaneous", "aoe": "One corpse or undead creature", "components": "V, S, M", "ct": "10 rounds", "save": "Depends on use (see below)", "save_type": "", "description": "Returns a recently killed person to life, or can be used to kill some undead with physical bodies (works on zombies, not ghosts).\nDetails:\n    Can only raise if death occurred within 1 day per cleric level. (You can still use it to kill an undead that died longer ago.)\n    Body must be sufficiently intact (missing head/heart causes failure).\n    The slain creature must pass a Resurrection Success roll based on Constitution (table 1.1.4a). Failure means no return.\n    Returned creature remembers dying but not the time spent dead.\n    Unless the GM rules otherwise: works on humans, half-elves, gnomes, dwarfs, halflings; not elves or half-orcs.\n    Returned creature has 1 hp, is weak/sick, and cannot fight/cast/work until bed rest of 1 full day per day dead.\n    Missing body parts remain missing.\nIf the target is an undead creature (with a physical body):\nIt saves vs spells/other magical effects.\n    Pass: takes 2d8+1 corrosion damage; no other effect.\n    Fail: returned to life if it died recently enough; otherwise it crumbles to dust.\n    A lich, or a vampire older than a century, automatically passes this saving throw.\nReversible as Slay Living:", "notes": "Returns a recently killed person to life, or can be used to kill some undead with physical bodies (works on zombies, not ghosts).\nDetails:\n    Can only raise if death occurred within 1 day per cleric level. (You can still use it to kill an undead that died longer ago.)\n    Body must be sufficiently intact (missing head/heart causes failure).\n    The slain creature must pass a Resurrection Success roll based on Constitution (table 1.1.4a). Failure means no return.\n    Returned creature remembers dying but not the time spent dead.\n    Unless the GM rules otherwise: works on humans, half-elves, gnomes, dwarfs, halflings; not elves or half-orcs.\n    Returned creature has 1 hp, is weak/sick, and cannot fight/cast/work until bed rest of 1 full day per day dead.\n    Missing body parts remain missing.\nIf the target is an undead creature (with a physical body):\nIt saves vs spells/other magical effects.\n    Pass: takes 2d8+1 corrosion damage; no other effect.\n    Fail: returned to life if it died recently enough; otherwise it crumbles to dust.\n    A lich, or a vampire older than a century, automatically passes this saving throw.\nReversible as Slay Living:", "link": ""}, "slay living": {"name": "Slay Living", "level": "5", "school": "Divine necromancy", "range": "30 ft", "duration": "Instantaneous", "aoe": "One creature", "components": "V, S, M", "ct": "1 round", "save": "Yes (negates effect)", "save_type": "", "description": "You speak an Abominable Word and point at a creature. Target may save vs spells/magical effects.\n    Pass: takes 2d8+1 corrosion damage; no other effect.\n    Fail: dies instantly.\nDetails:\nIn some campaigns, Abominable Words are lost secrets obtainable only through ancient lore, extraplanar consultation, or certain liches. Unless the GM rules otherwise, works on humans, half-elves, gnomes, dwarfs, halflings; not elves or half-orcs.", "notes": "You speak an Abominable Word and point at a creature. Target may save vs spells/magical effects.\n    Pass: takes 2d8+1 corrosion damage; no other effect.\n    Fail: dies instantly.\nDetails:\nIn some campaigns, Abominable Words are lost secrets obtainable only through ancient lore, extraplanar consultation, or certain liches. Unless the GM rules otherwise, works on humans, half-elves, gnomes, dwarfs, halflings; not elves or half-orcs.", "link": ""}, "true seeing": {"name": "True Seeing", "level": "5", "school": "Divine divination", "range": "Touch", "duration": "1 round per cleric level", "aoe": "120 ft radius around the touched creature", "components": "V, S, M", "ct": "8 segments", "save": "None", "save_type": "", "description": "Target sees things as they truly are within the area: detects illusions/displacements (and may choose to see through them), perceives astral/ethereal beings, hidden/secret things, sees alignment auras, recognizes polymorph/shapechange (and may choose to see true or altered form), and sees through darkness/bright light/fog/mist.\nDetails:\nGods and god-like beings, artifacts, and relics may produce effects immune to this spell.\nReversible as False Seeing:", "notes": "Target sees things as they truly are within the area: detects illusions/displacements (and may choose to see through them), perceives astral/ethereal beings, hidden/secret things, sees alignment auras, recognizes polymorph/shapechange (and may choose to see true or altered form), and sees through darkness/bright light/fog/mist.\nDetails:\nGods and god-like beings, artifacts, and relics may produce effects immune to this spell.\nReversible as False Seeing:", "link": ""}, "aerial servant": {"name": "Aerial Servant", "level": "6", "school": "Divine conjuration", "range": "10 ft", "duration": "1 day per cleric level", "aoe": "Nil", "components": "V, S, M", "ct": "9 segments", "save": "None", "save_type": "", "description": "Summons an aerial servant (invisible elemental being) and binds it to your service. Unless you or it travels to another plane, it magically knows the direction and distance to both the summoning location and your current location.\nDetails:\n    Spell fails unless you are on the Prime Material, Elemental Plane of Air, Ethereal, or Astral plane.\n    It cannot speak and knows no languages, but understands your spoken commands via the spell.\n    It hates being controlled; the spell compels strict obedience.\n    It does not have to obey:\n        commands that are obviously self-destructive, or\n        commands to attack a creature.\n    The servant is dismissed (spell ends) when: it is killed; you are killed; you dismiss it; you leave the plane of casting; or it leaves that plane.\n    Not evil, but it cannot cross Protection from Evil or a magic circle, and must recoil from a holy symbol held out by a cleric or paladin.\n    Nothing prevents it from attacking you; best practice is to stand protected until commands are complete.\n    If its mission can’t be completed, the spell ends; it is no longer commanded and will usually return and attack you.", "notes": "Summons an aerial servant (invisible elemental being) and binds it to your service. Unless you or it travels to another plane, it magically knows the direction and distance to both the summoning location and your current location.\nDetails:\n    Spell fails unless you are on the Prime Material, Elemental Plane of Air, Ethereal, or Astral plane.\n    It cannot speak and knows no languages, but understands your spoken commands via the spell.\n    It hates being controlled; the spell compels strict obedience.\n    It does not have to obey:\n        commands that are obviously self-destructive, or\n        commands to attack a creature.\n    The servant is dismissed (spell ends) when: it is killed; you are killed; you dismiss it; you leave the plane of casting; or it leaves that plane.\n    Not evil, but it cannot cross Protection from Evil or a magic circle, and must recoil from a holy symbol held out by a cleric or paladin.\n    Nothing prevents it from attacking you; best practice is to stand protected until commands are complete.\n    If its mission can’t be completed, the spell ends; it is no longer commanded and will usually return and attack you.", "link": ""}, "animate object": {"name": "Animate Object", "level": "6", "school": "Divine transmutation", "range": "30 ft", "duration": "1 round per cleric level", "aoe": "One object up to 1 cubic foot per cleric level", "components": "V, S", "ct": "9 segments", "save": "None", "save_type": "", "description": "Infuses a spirit into an inanimate object, which becomes a temporary creature that obeys you. When the spell ends, it becomes inanimate again; damage it took remains.\nDetails:\n    No self-preservation; obeys all commands even if self-destructive.\n    Statblock is “animated object” in the OSRIC GM Guide.\n    If the object is too large, spell ends without effect and the slot is still used.\n    Cannot speak/knows no languages; understands your spoken commands via the spell.\n    Spell ends if the animated object is killed; you are killed; you dismiss it; or you leave the plane of casting.\n    Commanding it does not take your combat action, but in any round you give it a command you can’t cast spells with a verbal component.", "notes": "Infuses a spirit into an inanimate object, which becomes a temporary creature that obeys you. When the spell ends, it becomes inanimate again; damage it took remains.\nDetails:\n    No self-preservation; obeys all commands even if self-destructive.\n    Statblock is “animated object” in the OSRIC GM Guide.\n    If the object is too large, spell ends without effect and the slot is still used.\n    Cannot speak/knows no languages; understands your spoken commands via the spell.\n    Spell ends if the animated object is killed; you are killed; you dismiss it; or you leave the plane of casting.\n    Commanding it does not take your combat action, but in any round you give it a command you can’t cast spells with a verbal component.", "link": ""}, "blade barrier": {"name": "Blade Barrier", "level": "6", "school": "Divine evocation", "range": "30 ft", "duration": "3 rounds per cleric level", "aoe": "Sphere of radius 5/10/15/20 ft around a visible target point", "components": "V, S", "ct": "9 segments", "save": "None", "save_type": "", "description": "Creates a stationary sphere of whirling blades around the target point; radius chosen at casting and cannot be changed.\nDetails:\n    Blades cannot penetrate rock or brick; they do not appear in those portions of the area.\n    Ends if you are killed or you dismiss it.\n    Blades are not magical; creatures only hittable by magical weapons take no damage.\n    Contact damage: 8d8 slashing, no attack roll, no save. Triggered when:\n        a creature enters or reaches through from either side,\n        the barrier appears on a creature,\n        a creature remains in it (damage at start of each round).\n    Barrier is narrow; standing adjacent is safe, but melee attacks through it cause damage.\n    Physical missiles/projectiles through it: -3 to attack roll. Magical/energy attacks do not take this penalty.", "notes": "Creates a stationary sphere of whirling blades around the target point; radius chosen at casting and cannot be changed.\nDetails:\n    Blades cannot penetrate rock or brick; they do not appear in those portions of the area.\n    Ends if you are killed or you dismiss it.\n    Blades are not magical; creatures only hittable by magical weapons take no damage.\n    Contact damage: 8d8 slashing, no attack roll, no save. Triggered when:\n        a creature enters or reaches through from either side,\n        the barrier appears on a creature,\n        a creature remains in it (damage at start of each round).\n    Barrier is narrow; standing adjacent is safe, but melee attacks through it cause damage.\n    Physical missiles/projectiles through it: -3 to attack roll. Magical/energy attacks do not take this penalty.", "link": ""}, "conjure animals": {"name": "Conjure Animals", "level": "6", "school": "Divine conjuration", "range": "30 ft", "duration": "2 rounds per cleric level", "aoe": "Up to 1 creature per cleric level (varies by strength chosen)", "components": "V, S", "ct": "9 segments", "save": "None", "save_type": "", "description": "Conjures animal allies at a visible target point. You choose desired strength (Weak/Medium/Strong/Mighty); stronger types yield fewer animals. GM rolls/chooses what appears.\nWeak — 1 per cleric level\n1–3 Baboon; 4–9 Dog; 10–16 Giant rat; 17–20 Jackal\nMedium — 1 per 2 cleric levels (round down)\n1–4 Badger; 5–14 Herd animal; 15–20 Horse\nStrong — 1 per 3 cleric levels (round down)\n1–2 Boar; 3–5 Camel; 6–7 Giant goat; 8–9 Horse; 10–11 Hyena; 12–13 Leopard; 14–15 Phorusrhacid (Axe Beak); 16–17 Stag; 18–20 Wolf\nMighty — 1 per 4 cleric levels (round down)\n1–3 Ape; 4–5 Bear; 6–7 Boar; 8–9 Bull; 10–12 Dire wolf; 13–14 Leopard; 15–16 Lion; 17–18 Sabretooth tiger; 19–20 Tiger\nDetails:\n    Spell fails unless on the Prime Material Plane.\n    Animals understand your spoken commands; need not obey self-destructive commands.\n    Ends when all are killed; you are killed; you dismiss them; you leave the plane of casting; or they leave that plane.\n    No XP for defeating them.\n    VTT spacing: GM may place; typical approach is one per unoccupied square in/adjacent to the target point. If no space, an animal appears later when space opens; duration extends accordingly for late arrivals.", "notes": "Conjures animal allies at a visible target point. You choose desired strength (Weak/Medium/Strong/Mighty); stronger types yield fewer animals. GM rolls/chooses what appears.\nWeak — 1 per cleric level\n1–3 Baboon; 4–9 Dog; 10–16 Giant rat; 17–20 Jackal\nMedium — 1 per 2 cleric levels (round down)\n1–4 Badger; 5–14 Herd animal; 15–20 Horse\nStrong — 1 per 3 cleric levels (round down)\n1–2 Boar; 3–5 Camel; 6–7 Giant goat; 8–9 Horse; 10–11 Hyena; 12–13 Leopard; 14–15 Phorusrhacid (Axe Beak); 16–17 Stag; 18–20 Wolf\nMighty — 1 per 4 cleric levels (round down)\n1–3 Ape; 4–5 Bear; 6–7 Boar; 8–9 Bull; 10–12 Dire wolf; 13–14 Leopard; 15–16 Lion; 17–18 Sabretooth tiger; 19–20 Tiger\nDetails:\n    Spell fails unless on the Prime Material Plane.\n    Animals understand your spoken commands; need not obey self-destructive commands.\n    Ends when all are killed; you are killed; you dismiss them; you leave the plane of casting; or they leave that plane.\n    No XP for defeating them.\n    VTT spacing: GM may place; typical approach is one per unoccupied square in/adjacent to the target point. If no space, an animal appears later when space opens; duration extends accordingly for late arrivals.", "link": ""}, "find the path": {"name": "Find the Path", "level": "6", "school": "Divine divination", "range": "Touch", "duration": "1 turn per cleric level", "aoe": "One creature", "components": "V, S, M", "ct": "3 rounds", "save": "None", "save_type": "", "description": "Touched creature magically knows the route to one specific destination you choose. If multiple routes exist, only the shortest is known. If none exists, you learn that and the spell ends.\nDetails:\nKnows the route, not precise distances/directions; cannot draw an accurate map. Learns nothing about hazards on the route.\nReversible as Hide the Path:", "notes": "Touched creature magically knows the route to one specific destination you choose. If multiple routes exist, only the shortest is known. If none exists, you learn that and the spell ends.\nDetails:\nKnows the route, not precise distances/directions; cannot draw an accurate map. Learns nothing about hazards on the route.\nReversible as Hide the Path:", "link": ""}, "harm": {"name": "Harm", "level": "6", "school": "Divine necromancy", "range": "Touch", "duration": "Instantaneous", "aoe": "One creature", "components": "V, S", "ct": "1 round", "save": "Yes (negates)", "save_type": "", "description": "You speak an Abominable Word and attempt to touch the target. If it fails a save vs spells, it takes enough magical damage to reduce its hit points to 1d4.\nDetails:\nIn some campaigns, Abominable Words are lost secrets. Affects normally living creatures only; no effect on golems, constructs, elementals, undead.", "notes": "You speak an Abominable Word and attempt to touch the target. If it fails a save vs spells, it takes enough magical damage to reduce its hit points to 1d4.\nDetails:\nIn some campaigns, Abominable Words are lost secrets. Affects normally living creatures only; no effect on golems, constructs, elementals, undead.", "link": ""}, "heal": {"name": "Heal", "level": "6", "school": "Divine necromancy", "range": "Touch", "duration": "Instantaneous", "aoe": "Creature touched", "components": "V, S", "ct": "1 round", "save": "None", "save_type": "", "description": "Target regains almost all lost hit points: up to normal total minus 1d4. Cures blindness, deafness, diseases, madnesses, and poisons completely. Ends feeblemind.\nDetails:\nDoes not raise the dead and does not remove lycanthropy. Affects normally living creatures only; no effect on golems, constructs, elementals, undead.\nReversible as Harm:", "notes": "Target regains almost all lost hit points: up to normal total minus 1d4. Cures blindness, deafness, diseases, madnesses, and poisons completely. Ends feeblemind.\nDetails:\nDoes not raise the dead and does not remove lycanthropy. Affects normally living creatures only; no effect on golems, constructs, elementals, undead.\nReversible as Harm:", "link": ""}, "hide the path": {"name": "Hide the Path", "level": "6", "school": "Divine enchantment", "range": "Touch", "duration": "1 turn per cleric level", "aoe": "One creature", "components": "V, S, M", "ct": "3 rounds", "save": "Yes (negates)", "save_type": "", "description": "Touched creature loses sense of direction; if it tries to move, its heading is randomly determined.\nDetails:\nIt can still attack and cast spells normally; only directional movement becomes random.", "notes": "Touched creature loses sense of direction; if it tries to move, its heading is randomly determined.\nDetails:\nIt can still attack and cast spells normally; only directional movement becomes random.", "link": ""}, "part water": {"name": "Part Water", "level": "6", "school": "Divine transmutation", "range": "30 ft per cleric level", "duration": "1 turn per cleric level", "aoe": "Path 10 ft wide; length 30 ft per cleric level; up to 1 mile deep", "components": "V, S, M", "ct": "8 segments", "save": "Depends on use", "save_type": "", "description": "Opens a dry pathway through a body of water (≤ 1 mile deep). No saving throw for this use. Can also be used to destroy water elementals.\nDetails:\n    Only bodies of water affected; does not function on the Elemental Plane of Water.\n    If targeted on/including water elementals: each must save vs spells/magical effects.\n        Fail: destroyed.\n        Pass: takes 6d6 raw magical damage.", "notes": "Opens a dry pathway through a body of water (≤ 1 mile deep). No saving throw for this use. Can also be used to destroy water elementals.\nDetails:\n    Only bodies of water affected; does not function on the Elemental Plane of Water.\n    If targeted on/including water elementals: each must save vs spells/magical effects.\n        Fail: destroyed.\n        Pass: takes 6d6 raw magical damage.", "link": ""}, "speak with monsters": {"name": "Speak with Monsters", "level": "6", "school": "Divine divination", "range": "Caster", "duration": "1 turn", "aoe": "30 ft radius around you", "components": 